UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'At last, you are complete.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Return with the trophy of your hunt.'
WHERE `entry` = 41632;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You may yet prove to be a decent $C after all.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Let us hope your pockets do not feel loose.'
WHERE `entry` = 41633;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Simply marvelous. A job well done. Thronda should listen well and follow your example. She has great potential, but her lack of discipline is a dire thorn in my side - and hers, too. Still, I can only partially blame her, for it is my sworn duty to her parents to foster her magical talent as much as her growth as a person.$B$BYou have my deepest gratitude, good traveler. Before you go, take one of these as compensation for the troubles. Be sure to step wary during these trying times.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How are your dealings with my tower faring?'
WHERE `entry` = 41634;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Is it done? Is this the head of their mongrel leader? Good riddance to them, their lot has chosen what path to tread - a path leading to their timely demise. I appreciate your courage, adventurer. Here, take this as reward for the good deed. With your actions, we may soon live our solemn lives yet again.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Stay safe, adventurer. Northwind''s hills are not meant to be drenched in the blood of the innocent.'
WHERE `entry` = 41635;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The crate from Mister Melain! I had met him on my short trip to Ambershire when I gathered the children for school, he told me what happened. Shocking that there are faithless heathens stealing from those who have already been dealt a bad hand by fate. The Light will shine upon you with benevolent rays for your heroic deed, good $C.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome to our humble church. Are you here to visit a lost one, or perhaps for silent prayer?'
WHERE `entry` = 41636;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Wonderful, their delighted expressions cast a smile on my own face everytime I see them. These children are the future of the Alliance, and it is our responsibility to prepare them for their own decisions as best as we possibly can. I will make sure the Church knows about your contributions today, good deeds will not go unnoticed. Did you learn something yourself, by chance? The island of Balor is a divisive topic within the kingdom, many of the superstitious dare not mention its name still. Regardless, it is part of our past and as such should be remembered.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How are you faring? I hope the little rascals aren''t too much to handle.'
WHERE `entry` = 41637;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oh, mother... I am so sorry to have left you in that lightforsaken place. Be rest assured, you will find a new resting place in Stormwind, my new home. Thank you - $N was it? With mother''s ashes returned, I will deliver them to the Church before continuing my duties here with Sister Argent. Farewell, kind soul. May the blessing of the Light shine your way.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'With the wars over, I thought Northwind may finally return to its peaceful roots. Maybe I have been too naive to think so.'
WHERE `entry` = 41638;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<The witch is cackling in an uncomfortable manner.>$B$BUseful after all. Here, some homebrewed potions of mine, just for you. You may stay a while and ask me anything. The woods have knowledge most don''t dare to ask...',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You better not question what I need these for.'
WHERE `entry` = 41639;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'There it is! I cannot thank you enough, truly! Had I lost these, I wouldn''t know if I''d be able to bear it. Everything in here are memories of the good friends I made during my time as a mountaineer, ones that visited me and my mountain rest whenever their duty took a toll on their bodies. For their sake, we have to reclaim it as soon as possible.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you been successful yet? Please, be careful and don''t act reckless on my behalf.'
WHERE `entry` = 41640;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A splendid display of your abilities, $C. I can see that you comprehend the fundamental teachings of shamanism, atleast when it comes to its utilization in combat. Thank you for lending a hand; I will relay what has happened to Far Seer Earthfury. It is our duty to nature and the spirits to ensure the elemental chaos is kept in check. It will take time, and perhaps your help again in the future, to uncover what Al''akir''s minions are scheming. Balance has to be maintained, at all costs.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Their hostility appears unreasonable. I wonder, what is their motive?'
WHERE `entry` = 41641;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'What a tragedy, Christoph was a truly good-hearted man and father. Seeing him succumb to such a senseless death breaks my heart. But what about poor, poor Arnold? I fear for him, now that he is orphaned. Please, let me take care of how to tell him of his father''s fate. The revered sister at the church of Ambershire will know what to say.$B$BThank you, kind soul. You''ve done a good deed today. May the blessing of the Light shine your way.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Mirabelle is lost deep in prayer.>$B$BO, Blessed Light, guide this lost lamb back into your fold. May his son not suffer the pain of solitude, may he be reunited with his kin and compatriots.'
WHERE `entry` = 41642;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Interesting. With the testimonies you''ve presented and my own information, we should be able to pinpoint potential suspects. Well done.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Operative Hawthorne is noting something down in his journal. With a stern expression of contemplation, he is lost deep in thought.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41643;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'This is troubling news. Not only does it confirm VanCleef''s schemes to run on a much grander scale, but we have to rule out the Defias being behind the rampant kidnappings. Leaving us to pursue a more grueling lead...',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The people of Northwind are wealthy. So far we haven''t received any ransom demands, but I would not rule out the possibility of that happening sooner than later.'
WHERE `entry` = 41644;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Again, a dead lead. We''re running out of options, deputy.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Our relationship to the Dark Iron is strenuous, to put it lightly. The Bronzebeard dwarves of Ironforge have a more... creative way to describe it.'
WHERE `entry` = 41645;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Operative Hawthorne lets out a deep sigh hearing your findings. Looking clearly exhausted, he begins rubbing his eyes as a sign of defeat.>$B$BThis whole ordeal proves to be more of a conundrum than I had hoped it would be. All three suspects act unrelated to our case, setting us back to zero. As much as it dismays me, I have to start my investigation anew. I will revoke your deputization; what you''ve done for me saved me valuable time, but I cannot demand any more of you. If I am fortunate enough, then the SI:7 will send someone to support me here. Until then, I must focus on my work. Farewell, $N.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'If you wish to assist in driving out the main force from Northwind, a local marshal is conducting his own operation in the Plump Pumpkin. You can find it to the southeast at Grimmen Lake.'
WHERE `entry` = 41646;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<The old woman is stirring her cauldron, which violently bubbles exuding a most pungent odor.>$B$BWell, well, well. What do we have here? A lost sheep trying to find a place to rest?',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41647;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oho, splendid, darling. The Widow''s Frills are especially thick this season, if we didn''t need them for now I would make a loveable stew out of them. They''re quite delectable, perhaps you can try them yourself once all of this is over. And this comb you''ve brought - it''s from a young woman. Let us not tarry any longer. Now then, to mix this all together...',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Now, now. Don''t let me wait too much.'
WHERE `entry` = 41648;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'If this bugger didn''t use a voice modulator, I would be able to tell you EXACTLY who he is. My big, green ears are the best in all of Azeroth, no fancy elf can compete with my auditive recognition!$B$BNevertheless, hearing the recording again may have in fact just helped us solve this mystery.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Remember: green, slider down and then turn the knob to the left!'
WHERE `entry` = 41649;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<The site that unfolds before only raises more questions. The leads you have are not many, but one sticks out the most: the Blood Elven dagger sticking out of the goblin''s chest. Your theory is that the blood elves you passed on your way southwest of here ambushed the goblin for an unknown reason. On their search for something they took the goblin''s possession along with the key to the locker they couldn''t find.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The site that unfolds before only raises more questions. The leads you have are not many, but one sticks out the most: the Blood Elven dagger sticking out of the goblin''s chest. Your theory is that the blood elves you passed on your way west of here ambushed the goblin for an unknown reason. On their search for something they took the goblin''s possession along with the key to the locker they couldn''t find.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41650;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Bizzbang Zipperbox?! That ole airhead was behind all of this? Frankly, his mind was one of the brighter ones when it came to engineering back on Kezan, but never in my wildest dreams would I have imagined him to hold such a grudge against me. This has me more baffled than a tauren at a barbecue! Even more curious is the device you brought me. I''ll have my technicians look at it, perhaps it can crack the code on that perpetual white noise still going.$B$BI gotta thank you for helping me out with this. With all the buzz going on here, I practically cannot leave this place - like ever. I got people to entertain! Here, take this as payment, you''re the hero for all my fans out there!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Hey, fella! You''re back - any luck finding Sir Incognito?'
WHERE `entry` = 41651;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oh, you heard the interference and are here to help? Perfect, I could use a capable pair of hands!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I''m a busy man!'
WHERE `entry` = 41652;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Speaking to the frog, its gaze drifts into the bog behind you. If not told otherwise, you would''ve guessed there were no thoughts behind its eyes. Yet, before giving up, the amphibian spirit bloats itself up, more and more, before releasing a cacophony of croaks and ribbits. Blown away, your mind is filled with visions of the world, some more ancient than the other. After the croakophony ended the frog spirit resumes its stance and gazes off into the distance once more.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The frog stares at you intently.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41653;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'These look wonderful, $N! I am impressed by your tenacity and display of skill. Truly, in the name of my forefathers, I thank you deeply. Now, let me conjure up a feast for everyone like they''ve never seen before!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My father and grandfather will not be the last generation to honor this tradition.'
WHERE `entry` = 41654;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Marvelous, $N. You''ve bested the dangers and braved them with courage and resolve. This token is proof of your conviction and willingness to tackle whatever struggle will come your way. I am certain, you will pave your future with the blessing of your ancestors, whom you''ve demonstrated your cunning today. Please, accept this as a boon for your achievement.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Don''t falter. You are more than ready for this task, I am sure of it.'
WHERE `entry` = 41655;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have come to claim your bounty have you?$B$B<Commander Aggnash lets out a hearty laugh.>$B$BYour actions this day may have saved lives within Shatterblade and for that you have my thanks. Your actions are worthy of the Horde, and even more worthy of reward.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What can I do for you $C?'
WHERE `entry` = 41656;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Commander Aggnash takes his time, studying the letter with some interest>$B$BIt would appear that the Dragonmaw Clan is not as united as we once thought. This news is relieving to hear.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it that you bring?'
WHERE `entry` = 41657;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Commander Aggnash looks on with a slight gaze of disbelief>$B$BYou were successful?$B$B<Commander Aggnash lets out a hearty laugh>$B$BYou have overcome your enemy, you have defeated Korlag! A mighty foe such as him was a dauntless task, and yet here you are, victorious. Be proud in your glory today, for you have done what very few could achieve.$B$BTake this, as a thanks from the Horde itself!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Preparation will be required if you desire success in the battle to come.'
WHERE `entry` = 41658;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Excellent work, the Sal''Galaz Mines hold quite a considerable amount of iron ore that should aid our efforts handily. Take this, as a reward for your actions this day.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How goes your progress $C?'
WHERE `entry` = 41659;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Glory and honor to your name! You have defeated our foe, and brought victory to the Horde. I have prepared a few items, take one and let it help on your journey.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you returned with the signets?'
WHERE `entry` = 41660;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I hope the poor merchant was simply robbed and not beaten for bloodŌĆöor worse. Alas, you have done your part, and for that, I am more than thankful. There is little I can offer, but take this. It was the last painting I did.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I miss holding a brush...'
WHERE `entry` = 41661;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Where the guards falter, the people shall provide. You have my gratitude, adventurer. A few coins for your trouble.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Dirt and gnoll spittleŌĆōI must burn these clothes.'
WHERE `entry` = 41662;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Mike, what a sly old fox. The man carries one of the most mediocre names I have ever heard, yet his mind could outwit any other intellect.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'More scrolls to read.'
WHERE `entry` = 41663;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'That utter, disgraceful dog. Bah, who would think that the laughingstock of children could be up to no good? Sir "Ambercheeks" is bold.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My shoulders feel heavy.'
WHERE `entry` = 41664;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Duke Sherwood is a close friend; many times he has denied the use of servants. It warms my heart to think he would find one in you. My armory is humble, and these are trying timesŌĆöat most, for your service, I can reward you with this.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Approach messenger, let me have what you carry.'
WHERE `entry` = 41665;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, there you are! Thank you, thank you. I believe they were going to dismantle my stall if you hadn''t shown up when you did. As promisedŌĆöa free pack of Amberglaze Donuts and an extra coin as a tip.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The people are literally rioting over the donuts...'
WHERE `entry` = 41666;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Hey $N, is she still looking at me? Bah, that woman makes me so uncomfortable. Anyway, did you manage to get the horseshoes? Oh, thank the Light. Here, take this and be quick about it. And, just in case, don''t show up during the tournament.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I will wipe that smile off her face.'
WHERE `entry` = 41667;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Hand them over; everything is ready. You may take an apple yourself for helping me out.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Ah, my poor Anduin.'
WHERE `entry` = 41668;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Grandmother sent you, and she said that? Oh, I miss her dearly. I can''t wait to try everything she sent me. I hear the donuts are very famous in Northwind. And I will treasure this toy from Mother forever. Thank you, adventurer. You have done me a great favor, and as Prince of Stormwind, I would reward you with something from our armoryŌĆöif I could. Instead, I will give you this book I have from the Archbishop.$B$BDo come and tell me of your adventures sometimes; this palace is dull and boring. I could use a friend.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You should speak to Miss Katrana or Bolvar, I am unable to say much.'
WHERE `entry` = 41669;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Some would tell you there is no meaning in thisŌĆöclinging to the dead, to the past, each day. Yet, these tombstones become mere decorations if the dead are forgotten. A grim fate, worse than death itself.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'No easy task, but a task all the same. May you walk with the Light.'
WHERE `entry` = 41670;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'With this returned, so too does hope return. During the gospel this year, we will reconnect with those whose faith has dimmed, for that is exactly what they need amidst the chaos enveloping these lands.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The fire was yet another test of faith.'
WHERE `entry` = 41671;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have my deepest thanks. There is little I can offer, despite all that big talk. With no visitors from outside Northwind, the inn barely gets a drunk or two. So, I offer you a warm meal, and you may choose any room upstairs and call it your own for as long as you are in Northwind.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I am counting on you.'
WHERE `entry` = 41672;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Whoa, it really is the size of her head! She will love it. Thank you; I will not forget this favor.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'She seemed very excited at the sight of the pearl.'
WHERE `entry` = 41673;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have slain that many? Good! Their blood will nourish the soil, and the grapes that grow from it will bear the sweet taste of victory.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I wish they would never experience a day of peace.'
WHERE `entry` = 41674;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Jerry came up with this? Not a bad idea. I gave the kid a hard time; I should go talk to him. Thank you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Orcs, damn orcs. ORCS!'
WHERE `entry` = 41675;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Without their leaders, the remaining orcs should return to their filthy lands.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Is it done?'
WHERE `entry` = 41676;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I heard them blowing up from here. Great job, pick one of these.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Need some flint and stone?'
WHERE `entry` = 41677;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good, here is your prize. May the Light smite you should you falter from its path.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you the chalice?'
WHERE `entry` = 41678;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'WhatŌĆöreward? And here I was thinking you were here only for the thrill of adventure. Here, have some coin.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I said charred bones, not coal.'
WHERE `entry` = 41679;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Argh, uerghŌĆōWIGGLES!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Uergh?'
WHERE `entry` = 41680;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Fleshy return with smelly orc.$B$BWiggles carry back to master.$B$BSmelly lost this, fleshy keep.$B$BBye fleshy.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Wiggles heard it! WOOSHŌĆōDONKŌĆōBONK!'
WHERE `entry` = 41681;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You may keep that pouch, I no longer need it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Dwarves are disgusting pigs.'
WHERE `entry` = 41682;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A job well done, and a reward well deserved.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Spare no second.'
WHERE `entry` = 41683;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So orcs were responsible after all; but not the Blackrocks. The way you described them doesn''t match with any recent encounters we had with any of the orc clans, at least not the ones I can recall by memory. We will take this to Stormwind and have the headquarters tackle this.$B$BRegarding the girl... I will see to it to retrieve her body myself; I need to see this orc camp either way. Leave telling her mother to me, it is nothing that should fall to someone like you anyway.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '$N? What brings you to me? You found the ones responsible?! Tell me!'
WHERE `entry` = 41684;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So Hawthorne deputized you as assistant for his investigations in Northwind. Let me see what results you have to show.$B$B<Shaw takes a thorough look through Hawthorne''s journal and an even more thorough read over the letter you have found at the orc camp. With a stern expression, he rolls the parchment and shows you the seal at the end of it.>$B$BThis is the seal of the Stormreaver Clan. This is an old orc clan we believed to have perished at the end of the Second War. I have read through this letter and what''s inside matches with the kingdom''s ailments: They issued the abductions of careless citizens, but turned their focus to Northwind for some unknown reason. Still, this is not the most alarming revelation about this whole ordeal. But first, a reward for your assistance.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What purpose do you have with the SI:7?'
WHERE `entry` = 41685;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'External forces, I reckon? We''re hard at work, so any new pair of hands is welcome.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41686;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Wonderful, just retribution for trespassing into my lands, raiding Birkhaven and ruining my mining schedules! They''ve got what they had coming for them! I must thank you. Here, choose something to your liking, someone of your caliber more than deserved it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Don''t you dare return without being drenched in ash and blood.'
WHERE `entry` = 41687;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The horse feed! Lady Mildenhall informed me someone has been tasked in retrieving the lost sacks from the gnolls. Am I relieved to see it all safe and mostly undamaged. We were running short on our old supplies and just feeding these horses hay does not provide them enough energy for the taxing physical exercise they have to fulfill in the tournament. Thank you very much again! Lady Mildenhall gave me some coin for you once you''ve finished her task, so please take it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Oh, Greetings. Apologies, but I can''t really spend any time on chit chat. Many of the competitors need their horses ready for practice.'
WHERE `entry` = 41688;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<You approach the poor thing with slow and careful movements. Greens in hand, you lay them gently in front of its bill, before witnessing it nibbling on the strands of grass. Distracting it with the strong aroma and flavour of the herbs, you have ample time to administer the bandage to its wing. Now that the wound is secured and the little one is strengthened by the greens, it keeps staring at you with an endearing look on its feathered face.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The round button eyes stare at you.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41689;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You were lucky, given you did not know what you fed this poor thing. The plants you picked are called Noble''s Pillow, infamous for their muscle numbing properties. They most assuredly helped ease its pain, yet there is still much to do if you want to save the little one.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Awfully busy today, wouldn''t you agree?'
WHERE `entry` = 41690;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<The old hag grinds up the herbs in a mortar before mixing in the gooey ambersap. Stirring the ointment, she applies it onto a new bandage. Carefully removing the old one, another batch is spread over the little ducks wound, much to its dismay. With quick but delicate movements the witch wraps the bandage around its left wing, securing it in place.>$B$BThere, darling; this will help it recover very quickly. Defenseless creatures like our friend here rarely have such luck at meeting a kind soul like you. And judging by its behaviour, it recognizes your efforts just as much. Your actions formed a formidable bond today. Make sure to foster it greatly, as power lies deeply rooted in such connections.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Don''t tarry too long, its condition won''t hold up forever.'
WHERE `entry` = 41691;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Your surroundings suggest a fierce battle has taken place here, the carrion birds lurking around the ruined camp paint a grim picture. The journal you find among the scattered supplies may hold a clue on what happened here.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Your surroundings suggest a fierce battle has taken place here, the carrion birds lurking around the ruined camp paint a grim picture. The journal you find among the scattered supplies may hold a clue on what happened here.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41692;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The Light be praised for your rescue. I thought I would''ve ended like the rest of the corps. Thank you again, I''ll tell you everything I know before getting out of this miserable place.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Oh, what a relief to see another $R! Please, you have to get me out of here! Their leader is on the top floors, a burly one, with an iron fist! She has the key; quickly, we don''t have much time!'
WHERE `entry` = 41693;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A pity, those were valuable agents we''ve lost today. I''ll send missives to their families, their service to the Kingdom won''t be forgotten. Now, regarding this scroll...',
    `RequestItemsText` = '$N, you''ve returned? Agent Deryl arrived here not long before you, his body strewn with grievous wounds. We''ve sent him back to Stormwind for recuperation. But tell me, is there anything you could find?'
WHERE `entry` = 41694;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I must say, it is thrilling to be on such a historical mission. The island of Balor is drenched in myths, legend and history. I can barely contain myself!$B$BOperative Gillian is a bit uneasy ever since we landed here, understandable, really. Not the most hospitable place. Still, we have a duty to fulfill, our service to the Alliance cannot be hindered by some measly ghosts. Either way, I take it you have something for me?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Hello, friend; how may I help you?'
WHERE `entry` = 41695;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I see you are back, with writings in hand! Splendid, really. Having a few more phrases to compare and reference will make this whole ordeal all the more quicker. What I was able to find out is that their way of encoding their texts is very similar to historical documents we have from the Second War. Which leads me to believe that we are dealing with remnants and survivors of said war. Interesting, isn''t it?$B$BRegardless, please let me finish the translation, it should not take too long, friend.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Gel''ror? No, no, no... Galbor? No, that''s not it, either...'
WHERE `entry` = 41696;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Mission accomplished. Well done, $C. Sadly, I suspect we cannot ultimately cut off the demonic forces here with their warlocks still up and running. But we take any little victory we can get. Remember, this is a war against numbers, gotta use what you got to your advantage! Speaking of advantage, this tablet you brought with you has to contain crucial information about the demon''s involvement in all of this. I just know it! I will bring it to Noppsy, he''ll know what needs to be done.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It is important to neutralize any threats before they can realize their full potential. Being two steps ahead of your enemy is a doctrine engrained in every SI:7 member.'
WHERE `entry` = 41697;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ohoho, fine handiwork, friend. Those demon-hugging orcs will be in for a surprise once we press this detonator here and all the explosive goodness is just flying all around them!$B$B<Rufus'' eyes are full of glee, to the point where he appears like an overly joyous bearded child.>$B$BHo, this reminds me of that one time I almost blew up the Dwarven District in Stormwind. I''ll share the story with you over an ale after we''re done brooding over this blasted island. An honest dwarven promise!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Too bad I won''t be able to see those beautiful explosions through all of this fog. I guess their sound will have to suffice for now.'
WHERE `entry` = 41698;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Verona is reading Noppsy''s report without changing expressions. Her meticulous analysis of the report reminds you why she is the spearhead of this operation.>$B$B$N, ready yourself. We will launch an infiltration.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Has Noppsy finished his translation? What have you found out?'
WHERE `entry` = 41699;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'My compass! Does that mean Verix got what he deserved? Good riddance to him, if you ask me. One goblin''s misery is another goblin''s fortune, as we like to say. With my compass back in my possession, all that is left is to repair the Gullwing into workable shape. Thank you for your help, $C. You can keep some of the coins that Verix looted. If you want to keep lending your hand, we won''t say no.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Verix'' greed cost me my beautiful zeppelin, he has to answer for his crimes!'
WHERE `entry` = 41700;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Excellent work, $C. These fiends may be horrors beyond our comprehension, but at least they have a delicious taste to them. We can survive a few more days cooking a fine gumbo with it. Either way, it seems we are not done dealing with them just yet.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Drench the seas red with their icky blood, but keep a watchful eye out for the roaming sharks around here.'
WHERE `entry` = 41701;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I have to admit, I''m impressed. The others and I were waging with how many limbs you''d return or if we''d have to fish your limp body out of the ocean. Guess I''ll owe Rikki some gold when we''re back in Booty Bay. Regardless, incredible display of skills by you. Yunie will be relieved to have one less issue holding us back. If you''re ever bored of adventuring around the world, the Steamwheedle Headquarters in Undermine are always in need of capable bruisers. Think about it, you''d fit right in!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The way they''re behaving makes you think there''d be something for them here, but for the love of me, I cannot fathom just what it may be.'
WHERE `entry` = 41702;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Color me surprised, a whole treasure trove full of valuable materials. This alone should suffice for rebuilding the outer frame of the Gullwing. I have to say, I didn''t expect you to be so successful. But that was to be expected for someone crazy enough to come to such a backwater island willingly, I suppose? Either way, we owe you one big time, friend. Goblin promise!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'We can''t spare too much time on the repairs, this humidity is not to be underestimated. I''d prefer if the zeppelins hull would not break halfway through Stranglethorn, so hurry up, yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41703;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Silence, not quite, but almost. My ghostly heart eases at your mercy. A noble deed of yours, truly. Had it not been for your kindness, the unrelenting torrent of their cries would have torn me into a vortex of insanity, that I am certain of. Balor''s curse may be perpetual, yet its effects are now ever so slightly diminished. You are in my debt, $C.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Their wailing haunts my undeath, a cacophony lamenting my incompetence as their lord.'
WHERE `entry` = 41704;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<You place the fragmented doll in front of the woman''s face and with a burst of unexpected ecstasy, her eyes widen as much as her brittle body allows it. With the last of her strength, she grasps the doll, with its edges digging deep into her hand, yet producing no blood flow. A last pitiful wailing is uttered before she stops moving entirely.$B$BWhether or not your last act made her death less painful, you can only guess. Atleast you can be certain that she is in agony no more.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Faint whimpering escapes her mouth.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41705;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'How vile... just being near them fills me with a burdening lethargy. This foulness is akin to what haunts our forests on Kalimdor, very much so. Yet still distinct enough to not be the same... I cannot fathom how painful it must''ve been to live with such a shadow in one''s body.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Shan''do Staghelm possesses the knowledge to uncover this mystery. It is our duty to help him prevent this darkness from spreading.'
WHERE `entry` = 41706;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Inspecting the mycelia under her monocle, Kinrial''s face is masked in a stern expression; you assume both concern and critical intrigue.>$B$BInteresting, the mushroom strains continue seeking fertile ground to propagate in. Under normal circumstances they''d quickly die if not nestled in fitting soil, but not these. They writhe and firm around, actively looking for nutrients. A harrowing sight. For our operatives'' sake, I will conceal this unsavory detail.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Kinrial doesn''t really pay attention to you.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41707;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'An unusally biting odor. Extracting a functioning poison from them might take some time, but the result will be worth the effort tenfold. I must thank you, your assistance accelerates the success of this mission more than you''d think.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You may think a medic indulging in poison distillation is uncommon, but this is a required expertise in the SI:7, regardless of designation. My knowledge over the body and anatomy in particular gives me certain insights others may lack.'
WHERE `entry` = 41708;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'This shine and texture...! Even in this small chip of it, I can feel the tides resonate within it. And you picked it up from an enormous pearl on an altar, crackling with energy? I''ll be honest with you, that sounds most alarming.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Kul Tiras and Balor share a history, were it not their ships to make trade with our fledgling nation many decades ago. As such I feel a distant connection and familiarity with this place, as faint as it may be.'
WHERE `entry` = 41709;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'That old fool. He always had a knack for living on the edge, but he should really start caring more about his safety. Either way, I am glad he is still in good health. Now then, my book may be a bit waterlogged, but I can formulate the spell nevertheless.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'From what we gathered I would assume the murlocs are collecting the shards of the broken pearl to complete it again. They do possess a degree of intelligence, more than enough to cast spells, yet even this is abnormal for what you''d expect from your regular murloc.'
WHERE `entry` = 41710;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Naga, you say?! This is truly bad news. If these slithering demons are behind this phenomenon, then I dare not think what their true intentions are. For now we have thwarted their ambitions. However, I do wonder, has this pearl been here all along? If so, was it always broken? And if not, why was it brought here; and by whom? The naga or the murlocs? Many unanswered questions still lie before us and none of them seem to be easily answered. Either way, I must thank you for your assistance. Our findings today helped me gain a better understanding of Balor''s unending storm. Once I return to Davenburg, I will send notice to the Council of Tides in Boralus about the pearl, as well as the naga''s involvement in all of this. With their ongoing incursions onto Kul Tiras, I am afraid this won''t be the last we''ve seen of them.$B$BPlease, take this as humble compensation for your deeds.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'All of this is more than puzzling, yet the situation calls for action, not speculation.'
WHERE `entry` = 41711;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Griselda is reading the dusty letter carefully, so as not to rip its paper with an unmindful move. A bittersweet expression hushes across the face, her eyes showing mild shock, but not the kind brought upon by bad news. Instead, a smile whisks itself upon her lips.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Can I help you with something?'
WHERE `entry` = 41712;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Breathtaking. The mysteries that will unfurl before my eyes while reading this ancient tome will be the key to our freedom.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You will know which grimoire it is once you''re near it. Its potent energies pour out of its pages even decades later.'
WHERE `entry` = 41713;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Ralwen grabs the reagents and places them in front of him. Quickly reciting the book''s chants, they begin to move and converge violently, releasing a powerful shockwave. What is left behind is an immaculate crystal.>$B$BBlasted magic, it did not work! I fear we need more energy for the chains to shatter. Do not fret, I am sure we will succeed eventually. As compensation for your deeds, please take the crystal we just created with you. I am certain it will prove to be useful in your journeys.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be quick, $N. We cannot wait any longer. Freedom is just a conjuring away!'
WHERE `entry` = 41714;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Are you headed back into the Scholomance, $N? You''ve already paid such a great price for the use of the Divination Scryer - perhaps you''d like to take another one with you. With it, you''d be able to face the perils of the Great Ossuary once more.$B$BBy all means, have it. You''ve certainly earned it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41715;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I saw you speaking with Commander Aggnash. What he speaks is the truth. We are under constant threat from a much more powerful enemy. The Dragonmaw have a grip over the region, and their power is unmatched. They outnumber even the dwarves of Dun Kithas by a significant margin.$B$BIf we want to truly make our place here, we will need to take action before action is taken upon us.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41716;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You''ve recovered them?$B$B<Advisor Ranagg snatches the orders from your hands, and quickly begins to read.>$B$BThese orders seem to contain plans for further invasions in the region.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Our security is in jeopardy every minute that you waste.'
WHERE `entry` = 41717;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So, they do intend to target us.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41718;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Commander Aggnash lets out a hearty laugh>$B$BYou have done well this day, Geshgan was a brutal enemy, and now he has fallen. You have served us well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Geshgan Blackhollow is a cunning foe, do not let your guard down.'
WHERE `entry` = 41719;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have done well, these have not been tampered by Dragonmaw hands... Go now, for I have research to do.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you recovered the documents?'
WHERE `entry` = 41720;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The day of victory has come at last, your actions have paved the way for the Horde to claim this land for itself. Thrall''s wisdom is clear in your actions.$B$BYou shall be rewarded for your work this day.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Our victory is at hand, make your way to Zarm''geth Stronghold!'
WHERE `entry` = 41721;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Would you look at the proportions of these?! These recluse legs will make a fine addition to the stock of food I have available. You''ve done me a great service, and everyone here in town.$B$BTake these coins, and go with honor friend.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you had any luck in finding those juicy legs?'
WHERE `entry` = 41722;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Your actions speak highly of your honor $C. The Wild Maw were a threat to be dealt with, and your actions has certainly eased our concern.$B$BTake this coin as thanks from the Horde.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What can I do for you $C?'
WHERE `entry` = 41723;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I am pleased. To think one would betray their oaths, friends, and loyalties for power sickens me to my core. You have done the Horde a service in rooting out such a vile traitor.$B$BTake this, may it aid your cause even further.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you found the traitor?'
WHERE `entry` = 41724;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such excellent craftsmanship, these components will serve me well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you recovered the Dark Iron Components, or are you just stopping by to say hello?'
WHERE `entry` = 41725;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such fine craftsmanship, you can tell goblin or gnomish hands touched such engineering.$B$BWith these parts I will be able to advance our efforts in Shatterblade Post even further.$B$BI must commend you for your work. Without the components and parts you have recovered this basecamp would be left in the stone age.$B$BTake one of these items, hopefully you will see use out of them.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you found the wrecks?'
WHERE `entry` = 41726;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The power of the Demon Soul is infused within this blood, its power is undeniable.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The blood is required for my rituals, has it been obtained $C?'
WHERE `entry` = 41727;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have done well, now we can begin the more arduous tasks.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you gathered what I have asked for?'
WHERE `entry` = 41728;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such dark, and powerful energy, it shall serve me well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Has my task been completed?'
WHERE `entry` = 41729;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Far Seer Mothang lets out a deep, and sinister laugh.>$B$BThe Pendant of Uth''okk, in my hands...',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you reclaimed the Pendant of Uth''okk for the Horde?'
WHERE `entry` = 41730;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The power of the Uth''okk gemstone is flowing through my veins... Such power is euphoric!$B$BI am reborn, and I have you to thank for doing all my work.$B$B<Far Seer Mothang lets out a deep, and sinister laugh.>$B$BThe Pendant of Uth''okk has been sapped of its power, but I am sure you can make some use of it.$B$B<Far Seer Mothang lets off a deep smirk.>$B$BFarewell $C.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Far Seer Mothang is lost in harmony.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41731;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Why what is this? Ancient technology from Grim Reaches you say? Such complex and intricate mechanisms...$B$B<Tarwegg takes a moment to inspect the device>$B$BI must say, this is an incredible find!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41732;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I have done some studying while you were gone, and looked over the mechanism. I believe I may have figured out at the least how to power it, but in its state of decay I cannot guarantee this will work.$B$B<Tarwegg takes the materials, and begins to power the Ancient Power Module within the mechanism itself. With a soft click, the machine begins to whirr into life, albeit, at a slow, and decrepit pace.>$B$BAha! I have done it, I thank you for bringing the relic to me to study and work on, may its power help you on your journey.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you gotten the required materials?'
WHERE `entry` = 41733;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'What is that you''ve brought, some sort of mechanical gizmo? I''d suggest you take that to a gnome, they know quite a lot more than the likes of me...$B$B<Jarkal takes a moment to study the mechanism>$B$BWhy, this be some of that Uldaman technology, not some gnomish trinket. I''ve seen something like this before here in the Badlands.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41734;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Torlag sent you? Bah he is always sending whatever fool he can persuade into hunting me local game. It is supposed to be him that is doing it.$B$BHere, take this silver. It was meant for Torlag, but since you are doing his work for him, you can take it instead.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Can I help you?'
WHERE `entry` = 41735;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have done well, this is the first step on the path to healing this land.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you gathered the Reachroot?'
WHERE `entry` = 41736;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such foul, malignant energy... The corruption in this land is evident.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Has your task been completed?'
WHERE `entry` = 41737;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The materials have been gathered. You have done your duty, now let me conduct mine...',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The land yearns for peace, and it is our responsibility to comply.'
WHERE `entry` = 41738;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You inquire about the Flame of Dagnoth? You say Yor''thegg sent you? You''re inquiring about dark and evil things, how do I know you''re not some minion of evil telling me a great lie?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41739;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Well done, you have proven yourself a capable adventurer! You have done me a good deed, and for that I will offer you the information you seek.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Has the scale been acquired?'
WHERE `entry` = 41740;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The Flame of Dagnoth is located in the Grim Hollow?$B$BI should have guessed.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41741;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I can feel it, the flames corruption has been snuffed.$B$BYour efforts here are monumental, and without your help I would have been left nearly helpless. In time, the land should heal, and the elements should rest. I shall remain to study this transformation.$B$BAs a thanks for your actions, I offer you a reward worthy of your effort. Go with honor friend.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I implore you to bring allies, for this evil may be to great to handle alone.'
WHERE `entry` = 41742;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A splendid choice. Should you ever itch for another game again, I''d be thrilled to test your mettle once more. For now, however, let me rest for a while.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Impressive, outright marvelous! It has been an awfully long time since I''ve been this challenged in the master''s game. My heartfelt thanks to you for providing the opportunity for so much delight and fun. A victor should not go without spoils, so allow me to bestow you a fitting reward for proving the grandeur of your strategic capabilities.'
WHERE `entry` = 41743;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A splendid choice. Should you ever itch for another game again, I''d be thrilled to test your mettle once more. For now, however, let me rest for a while.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Impressive, outright marvelous! It has been an awfully long time since I''ve been this challenged in the master''s game. My heartfelt thanks to you for providing the opportunity for so much delight and fun. A victor should not go without spoils, so allow me to bestow you a fitting reward for proving the grandeur of your strategic capabilities.'
WHERE `entry` = 41744;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Behold, a great power is now bestowed upon us. I never thought I would witness such a day when the sheer power of the goddess herself answered my call. The Scythe of Elune has been restored, and its power shall now lies within your hands to guard, and safekeep against the evils that encroach upon our world.$B$BWith such great power, shall come a great responsibility $C. It is entrusted upon you to uphold this artifact, and enact the will of Elune herself upon those that would threaten our purpose.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It is done.'
WHERE `entry` = 41745;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You''ve recovered the residue, nice work. I must say I was not so sure it was responsible sending some traveler to clean up our mess, but it seems to have worked out in the end.$B$BPlease, on behalf of us here, take these potions, they may be of use on your journey.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'We are working to ensure such a situation does not manifest itself again. When you recover the residue we can begin to channel any lingering energy back to the tower itself.'
WHERE `entry` = 41746;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The delivery of scrolls? Zaldimar must have sent you. I must admit, that I miss his presence at the tower, he was always such a skilled pupil.$B$BThese scrolls will be put to good use, I can assure you that. Please, take this, as a thanks from us at the Tower of Azora.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes, can I help you?'
WHERE `entry` = 41747;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A bright mind has been lost this day. In another world perhaps he could have truly been one of the great wizards of Azeroth.$B$B<Theocritus lets out a deep, and long sigh.>$B$BI doubt I will find another like him, and still, I must thank you for doing what must be done. Take this, as a personal thanks from me, to you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Ralthas has spread many secrets that are held dear to the Tower of Azora, he has aided the Defias Brotherhood... Such crimes cannot be left unanswered.'
WHERE `entry` = 41748;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'That''s what I''m talking about! This beauty will pay a pretty sum of gold with those Shadowfo-... Oh, you''re still here. Right! Your reward. Here, take this and some coin on top of it, you really made this goblin''s day!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Don''t leave me hanging, pal. You''re the fifth adventurer I''ve been tasking to get this damn stone.'
WHERE `entry` = 41749;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<You don''t have much time to react as you hand Grimbite the head of Gowlfang. With untamed wrath and hate, the gnoll tears the head out of your hand, before viciously biting into it, ravaging it into an unrecognizable state. After he is done, he tosses what is left into the near bog, letting it sink to the ground of the swamp. A yowling scream escapes Grimbite''s jaw, the other gnolls follow suit. The howling persists for a few moments, echoing throughout all of the Wetlands.>$B$BGowlfang is dead! Mosshide now truly free! You member of Mosshide, forever. Take this, for killing Betrayer.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Where is the head?! Head of Betrayer?!'
WHERE `entry` = 41750;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It is done. Life and death is a cycle that has to be maintained, and tainted life must be given the chance to bloom once more. The pain in my heart will continue to ache, yet I can be assured that Searistrasz is no longer in torment. Go in peace, mortal, and may your travels be without tragedy.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Even years later, the foul shadow of the Demon Soul haunts our flight.'
WHERE `entry` = 41751;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The acidic scent is overwhelming. There is no doubt that these spiders have been tampered with, magically enhanced by heinous rituals. You''ve done well in releasing them from their torment. Here, take this as a reward for the risk I''ve put you in. May you serve the warchief with pride and soul!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Dragonmaw orcs are psychotic remnants, clinging to the fading and misguided glory of our past. Decimate the fools while you are in their despicable lair.'
WHERE `entry` = 41752;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You are a faithful and obedient servant, $C. For your subservience, a reward awaits. Have this and be on your way, the Dark Lady does not appreciate needless loitering.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'These simpletons cannot comprehend the power they are meddling with. Once within our grasp, it can finally develop its full potential.'
WHERE `entry` = 41753;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The markings are undoubtedly dwarven, reminiscent of the times before even the War of the Three Hammers! If you give me but a moment, I should be able to translate the message written upon this tabletŌĆ”',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome to our grand exhibition! Please, if you have any questions regarding our displays, don''t hesitate to ask.'
WHERE `entry` = 41754;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A tablet about the Redbrand''s past?! Incredible; quickly, let me inspect it!$B$B<Torwyn adjusts his lens and begins perusing his gaze across the tablet''s stony surface. With each line he''s deciphering and reading, he''s becoming increasingly more red and sweaty, up until his hand is visibly shaking.>$B$BY-YouŌĆ”! WHERE DID YOU FIND THIS?! You will NEVER speak of this; never! No one is to know about this accursed tablet! Absolutely no one! Here, take this and your lips will remain sealed, am I clear?! Now begone!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Greetings, what brings you to the esteemed Redbrand Estate?'
WHERE `entry` = 41755;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good job, soldier. The more dead orcs I know of, the better I can sleep at night. It won''t be long before we''ve driven these mongrels out of the Wetlands for good. Keep fighting on, and you will always count on the aid of the sons of Khaz Modan.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Show ''em that the Alliance hasn''t lost its bite.'
WHERE `entry` = 41756;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good riddance. We''ve dealt a serious blow to whatever Dragonmaw remained in Khaz Modan. Now it is up to us to clear up the mess and dispose of any remaining vermin skulking around in our lands. I salute to you, $N. You''re a true hero in my eyes.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Don''t underestimate him. Beasts like him don''t survive by sheer luck.'
WHERE `entry` = 41757;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I sense something deep within the heart of this creature... It yearned for release, to combat a darkness that lurked.$B$B<Kym Wildmane looks confused, and lets out a slight sigh.>$B$BPerhaps my original assessment was incorrect. It was not the primitive dark magic of the quilboar that awakened this natural being and sent it into madness. No, it was something much darker, and sinister... I have more questions that I must research further. You have done well, regardless of my pondering. Please, take this, as a thanks from myself.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The lair of Razorfen Kraul is a twisted mess of bramble and thorn. I advise you prepare for the journey to such a place.'
WHERE `entry` = 41758;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such strange magic, I am unfamiliar with the lingering presence that drove these creatures.$B$BSuch energy is not of a natural origin. I must conduct further studies to find the truth. You have done well $N. Please, take these coins, may they serve you well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'When there are threats to the natural order we must do what we can to assist, and return balance.'
WHERE `entry` = 41759;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Frederik, old friend. Figments of your essence linger in this dull trinket, bare of any grandeur it once held. One day, when I may finally pass on and leave this realm, I will see you once more...$B$B$N, blessings upon you. This ring will find its way into oblivion, far away from the clutches of darkness, I will make sure of that. For your courageous act, take this from my remaining corporeal belongings. You deserve it well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The history of Balor continues to be written, where it will lead, I do not know. But this chapter of its past needs to be closed, that I am certain of.'
WHERE `entry` = 41760;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I expected nothing less. For an external aid, you''ve proven yourself to be a valuable asset to our team. If the thrill of adventure ever subsides within you, the SI:7 has room for individuals like you.$B$BPlease, report your findings. Time is running out.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not venture alone. These beasts are unpredictable and will stop at nothing.'
WHERE `entry` = 41761;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Wonderful, wonderful! Once they start up the stations again, they will create a SPECTACULAR display of pyrodynamics! With this outta the way, all we gotta do is haul the barrels back to... -wait, you''re still here? Oh, your reward, sure, just give me a second...$B$B<The goblin is rummaging in a small satchel on his belt, before pulling out a gold coin.>$B$BThere you go, don''t spend everything at once, bozo!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Are you done yet? Don''t keep me waiting, buster!'
WHERE `entry` = 41762;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oh, my beloved, finally back in my arms. I cannot thank you enough, $N. Now I have everything to enjoy my self-assigned vacation from the oil rig - thanks a bunch! Here, let''s share a drink and toast on the occasion!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'If you find it, don''t you dare open it! You are not ready for their... peculiar beauty.'
WHERE `entry` = 41763;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So the control panels were tampered with, hm? Not really a surprise, but a nuisance nonetheless. As much as I hate to admit it, our technicians will have to double proof them to ensure their original functionality is being restored. We wouldn''t want all this liquid gold just to blow up, alongside us!$B$BEither way, good work out there. Here, take these as compensation for the hassle; the Durotar Labor Union is in your favour!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How is it, any success with the pump stations yet?'
WHERE `entry` = 41764;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Must''ve been a breeze, eh? You are more competent than you look. Nert was right in allying with the Horde; not that he had much choice to begin with. Now that the fodder''s outta the way, time to smoke out their head honcho.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Done with the pest control yet?'
WHERE `entry` = 41765;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Shrillfluke, eh? Certainly not the biggest fish, but his name was popping up occasionally in Undermine. From what I can read here, their genius plan was to overload the pump stations using some home cooked spell - which of course backfired, typical goblin fashion. Instead all it did was power up the oil itself, leaving us with these troublesome oil oozes sludging around. Annoying, to say the least. Well, let''s put a bow on this thing, I don''t wanna waste another minute thinking about the Mogul''s cronies.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My workers are starting to enjoy their time-off a little too much. Let''s put an end to this and get back on our quota.'
WHERE `entry` = 41766;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You were in Tanaris and helped out Celdi? How wonderful, that woman is a true blessing! When she first flounced around Sparkwater Port my eyes almost flew out of my skull. A high administrator of the Bilgewater Cartel here, in our small town?! And she wants to join us?! It felt like I had just doubled all my lifesavings in a last effort try at the casino. After the disaster that was Blackstone Island, the Durotar Labor Union desperately needed an uplift in profit AND morale. The oil rig in Tanaris was an excellent idea, if I were to be so humble. With Slickwick at the helm, I just knew it''d be a success.$B$BDespite that, the Venture Co.''s continued sabotage and intrusion worry me. I fear their patience runs dry, Razdunk never was one to remain calm when he doesn''t get his way. Keep your ears and eyes sharp, $N. The future won''t be easy for us.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Either good news or no news, pal. Another bad errand would be the death of me!'
WHERE `entry` = 41767;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Does Lord Amberwood employ lowly peasants now to deliver royal documents? To be expected, but that matters little now.$B$BBe that as it may, you''ve done your assignment amicably. Still, my gratitude has limits. I have crucial information to analyze, so I would appreciate it if you would leave me to deal with the ailments of the kingdom in peace.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Lady Prestor pays you no attention.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41768;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Just as you are handing Jama''nali the quivering egg, its shell starts cracking. Piece by piece, the tiny hatchling fights its way out of its prison, gasping for air. With a high-pitched screech, the little one looks at you before jumping back into your hand, desperately biting the air.>$B$BRavasaur hatchlings are quick to stand on their own two feet, and are just as quick to grow hungry. To properly raise your new fosterling, we need to feed him.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The beasts will defend their brood viciously. Lack of caution may cause your journey to end prematurely.'
WHERE `entry` = 41769;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It is done. You''ve proven your determination to me. It is as clear as the sun how well you''ve been caring for your now adult Ravasaur. I am certain they think the same.$B$B<Your little hatchling has grown splendidly and is now a proper and matured Ravasaur. Still affectionate to you, it''s rubbing its jaw next to yours, causing no reaction from its venomous hide: you''ve successfully built a resistance to the lethal venom.>$B$BYour bond has reached a depth few others rarely hold. Be proud of your achievement and show it to the world. Now then, let me share the secrets of riding the Ravasaur.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It will be a long and arduous journey, but at the end the bond between the two of you will be stronger than ever.'
WHERE `entry` = 41770;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A good hunt. This should satiate its hunger - for now. These ravenous younglings crave sustenance all day long, so do not wait too long before feeding it again.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not hunt the Ravasaur, feeding it their poisonous flesh so early would kill it!'
WHERE `entry` = 41771;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Thick and heavy, brimming with power. My people have customs of eating powerful organs to enhance our own bodies. You should try it yourself one day, it can feelŌĆ” exhilarating.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The glands produce strong growth hormones. Yet fear not. Our little friend will not be harmed by consuming them.'
WHERE `entry` = 41772;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Bloodied and truly massive. These hearts will help the little one become a strong and robust adult when the time comes.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Their terrifying roar and massive claws will shred any unsuspecting hunter with ease.'
WHERE `entry` = 41773;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<The Pedestal of Unity begins to click, and whirr into motion. A humming of foreign magic begins emanate, and the surface of the stone begins to glow blue. From the base of the stone pedestal emerges a tray which contains a singular key.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The Pedestal of Unity stands unbroken, and free from serious damage. It is weathered from age, and covered in dust. Upon its surface lay ancient dwarvish runes as well as two slots that hold some sort of square objects. From a first glance, it is easy to notice some ancient mechanism is requiring the positioning of a specific item to activate the magic within.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41774;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'There it is; oh, how marvelous the binding is, so intricate and filigrane. Holding it in my hands is simply overwhelming, as if I am being cast between the tides of knowledge, tossed beneath the waves and drowning in Princess Aszune''s discoveries. You have done more than well, $R. As your reward, let me impart the wisdom of Aszune to you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Princess Aszune was an infamous figure in Highborne society; a mighty sorceress, she dedicated her studies on the power drawn from the astral planes of the Twisting Nether, oftentimes utilizing hazardous methods even her fellow astronomers would not dare use. After the Sundering, all traces of her had been erased and not even us Shen''dralar know what became of her.'
WHERE `entry` = 41775;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Lorekeeper Javon holds the crystal in one hand, the grimoire in the other. Reciting the incantations written on the pages, the nexus crystal begins to move, agitated by the swell of arcane power. Increasing in intensity, the rapid movements peak before breaking under vibrant purple sparks, leaving two golden shards in Javon''s hand.>$B$BSuccess! That was marvelous, truly! I am amazed how close to perfect Aszune''s spells are. With a bit of practice and refinement, we will be able to quickly and more safely break apart nexus crystals with ease.$B$B$N, thank you for your cooperation. You can keep these shards as a reward for your assistance. Please, bring me any nexus crystal you can find, so that I may continue my experimentations.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Nexus crystals are the concentrated arcane essence of the Twisting Nether that seeped into the armaments and artifacts of Azeroth. They possess immense power and potential and are used in many magical enchantments that empower the recipient tremendously. Usually these crystals are so dense that not even the strongest spell or weapon can break them without releasing a volatile and lethal explosion. Aszune, however, managed to create a method of splitting a nexus crystal into two lesser magical shards, maintaining its stability and energy.$B$BI would love to conduct experiments with the instructions found inside Aszune''s manifesto. Bring me one such crystal and we will see how true her words will ring.'
WHERE `entry` = 41776;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Crackling energy shoots out from the magical shards, while Javon recites the spell. Heat begins to emanate from his hand and the pieces begin to form a liquid union, hovering slightly in the air. Shortly after, a burst of mana erupts - and in Javon''s hand lies a nexus crystal.>$B$BSplendid, seeing it unfold right before my eyes is something I will remember forever. To think what we''ve achieved today was only possible because of ten-thousand year old knowledge, wisdom my people treasured for millennia is a testament to our resilience. Don''t fret, young $C, without your aid, all of this would not have been possible. Please keep the crystal as your reward. I am adamant that we can refine the process even further, so I would be pleased if you''d gather the needed components once again.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'In her dissertation, Aszune theorizes that arcane energy naturally coalesces after some time. This, however, could be accelerated in an albeit unnatural way. She wrote that if attuning two similarly inclined implements to the same wave of energy, they would eventually fuse, creating something wholly new. My desire to try this on my own is indescribable. Let us begin with something simple for now; who knows what kind of dangerous repercussions our actions may bring with them. Following these incantations, I will attempt to coagulate two brilliant shards, creating something magnificent. $N, if you could deliver me these shards, it''d be much appreciated.'
WHERE `entry` = 41777;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, the Libram of Voracity. Have you browsed its pages? For the unkeen eye, it is merely a collection of disconnected images and cryptic words, but for the enlightened, unforeseen potential lies within. The Athenaeum is greatly indebted to your continued assistance.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Athenaeum houses a near endless multitude of tomes and books, filled to the brim with millenia old knowledge. Naturally, this attracts shady individuals intent on pilfering our esteemed collection for their own personal gain. Much to our dismay, this has become a daily occurrence, and my fellow archivists are barely bothered by it. Please, if you find any of our lost librams inside and outside of Dire Maul, return them to me.'
WHERE `entry` = 41778;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, the Libram of Constitution. This heavy tome is infamous for harboring difficult incantations and invaluable arcane wisdom some would deem as perilous. The Athenaeum is greatly indebted to your continued assistance.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Athenaeum houses a near endless multitude of tomes and books, filled to the brim with millenia old knowledge. Naturally, this attracts shady individuals intent on pilfering our esteemed collection for their own personal gain. Much to our dismay, this has become a daily occurrence, and my fellow archivists are barely bothered by it. Please, if you find any of our lost librams inside and outside of Dire Maul, return them to me.'
WHERE `entry` = 41779;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, the Libram of Resilience. A popular oeuvre among aspiring arcanists. But beware, should you lose yourself within its pages, there is no turning back. The Athenaeum is greatly indebted to your continued assistance.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Athenaeum houses a near endless multitude of tomes and books, filled to the brim with millenia old knowledge. Naturally, this attracts shady individuals intent on pilfering our esteemed collection for their own personal gain. Much to our dismay, this has become a daily occurrence, and my fellow archivists are barely bothered by it. Please, if you find any of our lost librams inside and outside of Dire Maul, return them to me.'
WHERE `entry` = 41780;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The Libram of Rumination. A nefarious grimoire. I''d best not disclose its contents, and for your sake, I wish you did not open its accursed pages. The Athenaeum is greatly indebted to your continued assistance.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Athenaeum houses a near endless multitude of tomes and books, filled to the brim with millenia old knowledge. Naturally, this attracts shady individuals intent on pilfering our esteemed collection for their own personal gain. Much to our dismay, this has become a daily occurrence, and my fellow archivists are barely bothered by it. Please, if you find any of our lost librams inside and outside of Dire Maul, return them to me.'
WHERE `entry` = 41781;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, the Libram of Tenacity. If our statistics are to be trusted, this appears to be the book that has been stolen the most. I wonder why... The Athenaeum is greatly indebted to your continued assistance.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Athenaeum houses a near endless multitude of tomes and books, filled to the brim with millenia old knowledge. Naturally, this attracts shady individuals intent on pilfering our esteemed collection for their own personal gain. Much to our dismay, this has become a daily occurrence, and my fellow archivists are barely bothered by it. Please, if you find any of our lost librams inside and outside of Dire Maul, return them to me.'
WHERE `entry` = 41782;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Placing the books on Noppsy''s table, the gnome marvels at the proportionally gigantic tomes.>$B$BSo beautiful and ancient! It will take some time to study these documents thoroughly. Thank you, $N. You''ve done a great service to the kingdom today, preserving part of their history, as ugly and depressing as it may be. These stories tell us valuable lessons, so barring your eyes from them will only hurt you in the long run. Remember, knowledge is key to your survival.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Balor was a place of hardship, tribulations and tragedies. Born from the wish for independancy and wealth, it quickly became the haven for merchants across the kingdom, and even those beyond its borders.'
WHERE `entry` = 41783;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So, maybe you do have the stuff. Well, if you''re willing to hand the coin over, I''ll open my secret vendors list for you, and all the others who have paid my fee. Trust me, you won''t regret it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Got the coin?'
WHERE `entry` = 41784;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Nydiszanz recoils and hisses in pain at the sight of the Demon Soul shard. Just being near it causes a visceral reaction by him.>$B$BImpossible, you retrieved it and dare bring it to us?! I donŌĆÖt know if you are reckless, cruel, gullible or all of the above. But... you being here... with it... It means the Dragonmaw are no more. Their warchief returned to the cycle, their machinations thwarted. And the Demon Soul returned to us. Even through all its taint, I can sense the QueenŌĆÖs benevolence somewhere hidden within, reaching out...$B$B$N, hand me the shard and I will deliver it to our Queen. Only she is capable of destroying the last remnants from this dark hour of our past. For you, I present these. A just reward for your sacrifice in stopping the Dragonmaw and ending the terror of the Demon Soul. Use it well, mortal.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'This aura...! It cannot be!'
WHERE `entry` = 41785;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It was a matter of time till someone dares to venture here. Lower your weapons, I mean you no harm.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41786;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'What travesties have transpired at this place...? Never have I witnessed such horrors in my life, the thought of such profanities even existing send shivers down my spine.$B$B$N, your bravery in descending this spiral of madness is a heroic feat rarely seen nowadays. Your service to the kingdom and all of the Alliance this day will be remembered by those present and cherished by those affected. These rewards do not match the magnitude of your deeds, but take them nevertheless.$B$BYou are dismissed.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It may be too much to ask from you, but we don''t have any luxuries left at this point.'
WHERE `entry` = 41787;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So... Kyra has finally deigned to remember I exist? How endearing.$B$B<Drethanis regards you with a calm, unreadable gaze ŌĆö no warmth, no gratitude.>$B$BVery well. If nothing else, your presence may serve a purpose. The rot runs deeper than any of us feared.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Finally.'
WHERE `entry` = 41788;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Their spirits now drift back to the Dream... to merge with Ursol, the Bear-God they worshipped with such fervor.$B$BHow ironic. For all their blind devotion, even Ursol could not shield them from corruption. Or perhaps... he chose not to.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Time is of the essence ŌĆö do not waste it.'
WHERE `entry` = 41789;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So... it is done. A necessary task, and performed adequately.$B$B<He pauses, gaze drifting toward the tainted moonwell, voice lowering with unease.>$B$BAnd yet... a shadow lingers in my thoughts.$B$BWhat if Ursol himself has fallen? What if the silence is not from disdain, but from madness... corruption?$B$B<His tone grows cold, edged with quiet alarm.>$B$BA dangerous thought. One I dare not entertain lightly. The Archdruid must hear of this.$B$BYou have my thanks for your... assistance. May the winds carry you far from this cursed place.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be wary, $C. He is a formidable enemy.'
WHERE `entry` = 41790;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Stand tall, soldier. Belgrom did well in sending you here. Look around, there is much to be done here.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41791;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'That smell...! It must be Slagg''s famous hog steak! I could recognize that smell from anywhere. It''s just like how our father used to cook it. Thank you very much, $N. Being so far in enemy territory sometimes takes a toll on my morale. I appreciate you and Slagg reminding me what we are fighting for here.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Don''t cause trouble around here, we''ve got our hands full already.'
WHERE `entry` = 41792;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Throm''ka, young one. Welcome to Shatterblade Post.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41793;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Mok''thardin did good in sending you here. This potion will prove to be vital in our endeavors on this island. While you are here, aid us. We could use any hand available.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Thrall hall, youngling. What brings you to Stormbreaker Point?'
WHERE `entry` = 41794;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Whelpling, what we are facing is an abyss of unseen depth. Be absolutely sure your heart is steeled for what is to come. Lest you''ll be devoured by the void festering on this island.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41795;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Scarves from our father? Oh my. Now this is a bit embarrassing. He''s always been on the softer side of things, a dreamer, you could say. Don''t get me wrong, though. I appreciate it very much. Alessa and I grew up in Stormwind. Since we were very little back then, we don''t have many memories of the time, but it still feels weird for us to be back here. Having something familiar from home will help us with the situation, for sure. For that, you have my thanks.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Anything I can help you with? I need to prepare for the tournament, our opponents won''t be easy to defeat.'
WHERE `entry` = 41796;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A letter from Avette? How is she? I heard Duskwood is a treacherous place nowadays, not safe for any of the common folk.$B$B<Barbara opens the letter and quickly glances over a few lines. While doing so, a chuckle escapes her.>$B$BI see I have nothing to worry about, how relieving. It''s been too long since I''ve heard from her and I was beginning to assume the worst. Once Northwind''s troubles subside, I will pay her a visit. It is more than overdue. Here, take these few coins as thanks from me and Avette. Trust me, you did more than you think for the both of us. Stay safe on your travels, $N.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How can I help you? Need to refill your quiver?'
WHERE `entry` = 41797;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oh Ronald, your heart is in the right place, but your naivete is just too cumbersome sometimes. Either way, now that you''re here, you might as well assist us. My name is Operative Verona Gillian, and I welcome you to the hell that is Balor.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Ronald Gillian asked you to join his wife on Balor to assist in her work.'
WHERE `entry` = 41798;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Hornby sent you? That fool is too soft for his own good. I appreciate the sentiment, but what is happening here exceeds whatever I was assigned to in Davenburg by far. Out of the question. He is right in one thing, however. Should you aid me in my research, I''d be quicker to return to the mainland. So, what do you say?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Speak with Hydromancer Finnigan in the SI:7 Outpost on Balor.'
WHERE `entry` = 41799;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Let''s hope you gave those restless spirits the peace they deserve. The dead should stay dead, especially ones who fought and bled for their kin.$B$BStillŌĆ” makes you wonder, doesn''t it? What twisted thing got into that tomb and stirred everything up? There''s something dark at work in those mists, and I''ve got a bad feeling this ain''t the last we''ve seen of it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Careful out thereŌĆöGrim Hollow''s not the kind of place you just stroll through. The mist hangs thick, and the shadows feel... off, like they''re watching you. Plenty of brave folks have gone in thinking they''d be fineŌĆömost never came back. Would be a damn shame if you ended up buried with the Wildhammer dead instead of helping them.'
WHERE `entry` = 41800;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Who am I? Ah, you mortals and your curiosity. I have been known by many names across the ages, but you may address me as Sarthyss Scaleheart. It is not by mere chance that you have wandered into my domainŌĆöno, this meeting reeks of fate''s design.$B$BAnd as it happens, mortal, I find myself in need of assistance that only hands such as yours can provide. Strange times, indeed, when a dragon must turn to the fleeting for aid.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'A mortal? Here? Speak your mind quickly.'
WHERE `entry` = 41801;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A dark ritual? A cursed dwarven sorcerer? Mortal, you speak of things beyond your understanding. That is no mere dwarfŌĆöit is a skardyn, a twisted and vile abomination, once kin to dwarves but long since fallen into darkness.$B$BAnd if the skardyn walk these lands once more, it can mean only one thingŌĆöthe gates of Grim Batol have been opened again.$B$BThe noble draconic defenders who once stood vigil over that cursed place have succumbed to madness, their minds broken by the lingering corruption of Modgud. Her shadow stretches forth once more, reaching to taint the world anew. This is no mere threat, mortalŌĆöthis is calamity given form.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I cannot say what horrors await you in the depths of the Tomb of Ancestors. The corruption that festers there is ancient and powerful, far beyond the reckoning of most mortals. Prepare yourself well before you venture forth, and heed this warningŌĆödo not let foolish heroics guide your actions. Caution and wisdom will serve you far better than reckless bravery.'
WHERE `entry` = 41802;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Now you see the truth, mortalŌĆöclear as the moon over the frozen peaks. This skardyn sorcerer must be struck down before his vile work can seep further into the heart of this land. His very presence here is no accident; it is the herald of greater darkness, the echo of a curse long thought buried beneath stone and time.$B$BWhatever foul purpose brought him to Grim Hollow, it festers like a woundŌĆöand if left unchecked, its rot will spread. These swamps, already choked with corruption, are but the beginning. Mark my words: the magic he weaves will not stop here. It will slither beyond the Hollow... to Dun Kithas, and perhaps even farther, poisoning the land, the skies, the very soul of Khaz Modan.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Dire times indeed.'
WHERE `entry` = 41803;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ahhh... Of course it would be the searing kiss of the Red Flight that could sunder such foul sorceries.$B$BThe Skardyn''s wards are woven with the brittle cunning of earth and shadowŌĆöstrong against conventional magic, yes... but against the raw, devouring fury of my crimson cousins?$B$BI should have seen it soonerŌĆöfire has ever been the answer to vermin who burrow too deep.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'While you seek their knowledge, I shall reach out to my dragonflight. Perhaps among our ancient scrolls and hidden memories, we can uncover some forgotten truth. But hurry. The shadows grow bold, and time is not our ally.'
WHERE `entry` = 41804;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Mmh... You have done what was necessary, mortal.$B$BTheir minds are finally still. No more Skardyn whispers. No more chains of twisted magic. Only silence... and the long sleep they were denied.$B$BDo not mourn them. Their fire now fuels our purposeŌĆötheir last act will burn brighter than their madness ever did.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The whelps are no use to us- you must find the adult kin.'
WHERE `entry` = 41805;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Dragonfire bombs? Ha-HA! Now you''re speaking my language!$B$BYou''ve come to the right gnome, friend! Oglethorpe Obnoticus at your serviceŌĆöchemist, engineer, part-time arcanomechanical theorist, and full-time enthusiast of all things that go BOOM!$B$BBuuut let''s not get ahead of ourselves. Sure, I can whip up a dragonfire bombŌĆöof course I can! But as it stands, I''m a bit... let''s say, under-equipped. Supplies, reagents, blastproof gogglesŌĆöthe usual!$B$BSo! If you''re ready to lend a hand, we just might make a little history together. A very explosive bit of history.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it? I''m rather busy!'
WHERE `entry` = 41806;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Oglethorpe adjusts his goggles and inspects the materials with exaggerated precision>$B$BOoooh, yes! The powder''s potent, the framework''s solid, and the gizmo''s got just the right amount of whirrrr. Excellent work! These will do nicelyŌĆöno duds, no rust, no strange gooey residue. Always a good sign!$B$BNow stand back, friendŌĆöway backŌĆöand prepare to witness engineering brilliance in action! I shall now craft... the BOMB OF THE AGES!$B$B...Heh. Just, uhŌĆöquick question before I start the final assembly.$B$BYou''re not planning to use this in town, are you? Or on, say... anyone I know? Or me?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Got the materials? Hurry!'
WHERE `entry` = 41807;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'In your absence, there has been much disturbance. Strange lights, flickering with unnatural hues, have danced from the depths of that cursed crypt. The air itself trembles with arcane dissonance. Whatever stirs beneath... it grows stronger.$B$BIt is good that you have returned. We are running out of time.$B$BMay the gnome''s contraptionŌĆöchaotic though it may beŌĆöcombined with the sacred fire of my kin, be enough to quell the abomination that waits below. If it is not... then the consequences will echo far beyond these hills.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You have finally returned, mortal. I hope you bear good tidings.'
WHERE `entry` = 41808;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'At last... the taint lifts.$B$B<His wings flex slightly as the oppressive weight of dark magic dissipates, the air itself seeming to sigh in relief. The swamp''s murky waters ripple as if awakening from a long nightmare.>$B$BGrim Hollow will mend. The earth remembers how to heal... given time.$B$BYet this victory is but one ember plucked from a wildfire. The Skardyn do not act aloneŌĆöthey are rats fleeing a sinking nest. Grim Batol has spat out more of their kind, scattered like rot across Khaz Modan.$B$BAnd worst of all... they scurry with purpose. This was no mere exile. They serve something. Something old. Something hungry.$B$BMark my words, mortalŌĆöthis is not over. Whatever they plan... we must find it before it finds us.$B$BAnd next time... the fire we bring may not be enough.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Time is of the essence.'
WHERE `entry` = 41809;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It is done. This Verdant Rune is tethered to the essence of the World Tree in conjunction with the Runestones. Focus your mind on its potent magic, and your spirit will find itself anew here, at the foot of Nordrassil.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'With the Runestones restored, we can utilize their Dream energy to aid us in this war against the Nightmare. In times immemorial, the keepers of the wild and their protectors used powerful runes, much like the Runestones you had just brought back to life. With them, they could attune their spirit to a point and travel there posthaste via the Emerald Dream. If you wish, I can carve such a rune into a small dream shard, so that you may heed our call for help wherever you may be on Azeroth.'
WHERE `entry` = 41810;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Finally, a silence I have not heard in some time, the dunes themselves are at peace, and so am I... My wandering has come to an end, and perhaps it may be time to find peace for myself. I thank you traveler, you have done this place a great service. I offer you what little I can, may it serve you well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Silence, you be interrupting the winds...'
WHERE `entry` = 41811;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such beauty- such magnificence. I wish I could have personally laid eyes upon the ancient tree, though I thank you for the efforts you have taken to recover this. I am within your debt. Please, on behalf of us druids, take this as thanks.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Travel carefully, the depths of Blackfathom are crawling with evil.'
WHERE `entry` = 41812;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Magni''s beard, an entire crate of it! So lucky this stuff doesn''t go bad easily. Here you go, have some yourself.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Hope it''s worth the trouble, eh?'
WHERE `entry` = 41813;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'While in poor condition, it is still the crown of a duke. This will prove those rascals in the Halls of Explorers wrong! Thank you, $R. Here is what I promised.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Did you come up with something?'
WHERE `entry` = 41814;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good coin comin'' from these. Got your cut right here.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'No guts, no glory.'
WHERE `entry` = 41815;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I smell blood in the air. You wear it like a second skin now. Good. Bring those tails hereŌĆöwe will feast on them.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Go out there and prove to yourself that you are the predator, not the prey.'
WHERE `entry` = 41816;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Your fear did not win today. Your eyes have changed, they look calmer now.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Life is a battle, a battle against the aspects of your being that you cannot fully control.'
WHERE `entry` = 41817;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I am proud of the hunter you have become. Choose something of mine to carry as a memento of your success.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Your final task awaits.'
WHERE `entry` = 41818;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The irony of this scroll is lost on me.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Slithering snakes, self acclaimed rulers of the seas and oceansŌĆö-a pain to deal with.'
WHERE `entry` = 41819;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'O''jin is on the right path; he has done well to send you instead of coming himself. A chieftain must know how to make the proper choice. This is valuable information, and for your trouble, a reward is due. There may come a time when I will seek your aid in dealing with this issue. I will return to my duties and soon speak with the Warchief. Beware of the shadows, $N, especially where they dance freely.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'There is little time to spare. Speak.'
WHERE `entry` = 41820;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I will light a torch and perform a ritual to guide their souls to the afterlife. Thank you for setting them free.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It''s so loud...'
WHERE `entry` = 41821;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A mercy far too great for scum like them. Take these; they will carry the light of An''she with you through grim lands.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'In time, An''she will return to these lands.'
WHERE `entry` = 41822;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have my thanksŌĆöand with them, a reward.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'This task can wait, but I would rather you fulfill it as quickly as possible.'
WHERE `entry` = 41823;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have brought me its core? Well done. I will attempt to purify it now.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Earthmother will guide you to the answer.'
WHERE `entry` = 41824;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Uda''pe was right to send you to me. Though we are not very fond of working with the Horde, you have my thanks and will be paid accordingly.$B$BI will even add a bonus for being so silent and respectfulŌĆöUda''pe taught you well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Speak.'
WHERE `entry` = 41825;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Mindless undead. Some are nothing more than flesh waiting to be cut down; others, the lingering essences of those who wereŌĆöforever trapped. You have fulfilled your task.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'None are deserving of such a cruel fate.'
WHERE `entry` = 41826;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Mok''gun''s fate was sealed by Gul''dan. He was not the first nor the last. Rest easy, stranger. This old wanderer has no quarrel with you or your kin. I am Drak''thul, once a powerful warlock of the Stormreaver Clan. Now I am here to make sure I am the last of my kind.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Awful day for a swim.'
WHERE `entry` = 41827;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Stand proud child of the Horde. Victory is honorably achieved by those with strength and thunder in their blood.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Done yet?'
WHERE `entry` = 41828;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good. Now I shall burn these wretched eyes, so the last thing their souls gaze upon is the fiery pits of the afterlife they deserve.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I am prepared to set them aflame.'
WHERE `entry` = 41829;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I see the color of blood and smell the stench of death on you. Well done. Now, onto other matters.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'We owe apologies to none. It is not guilt that brought us hereŌĆöbut honor.'
WHERE `entry` = 41830;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Today, you have been the consequence of others. One day, your own will find you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How thin the line between arrogance and confidence can be.'
WHERE `entry` = 41831;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You know victory like no otherŌĆöI''m half a mind to challenge you myself.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The queens of the colony are close. Keep a level head and push forward.'
WHERE `entry` = 41832;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Well, what do you know... a ray of sunshine breaks through.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Ashes to ashes, dust to dust and scum to scum.'
WHERE `entry` = 41833;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Though it is not bound to be the last time we see the embers of the Shadow Council, a great victory was won. While we wish nothing from the land of Balor, it has given me the greatest gift.$B$BKilrogg was spiteful in the beginning, jealous of Grommash''s celebration as a heroŌĆöwhile he himself seemed forgotten. But he was wrong to envy Grommash. My older brother merely set the foundation. It is you, and I, and Kilrogg who will build our future. I am glad he sees it that way now.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Lok''tar ogar.'
WHERE `entry` = 41834;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A step closer to the true goal.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Legion or not, do what must be done.'
WHERE `entry` = 41835;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Drak''thul cracks the box open.>$B$BWhat is this...?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I wonder what sort of dark, twisted artefact she holds that can provide her ownership of a copy of the key.'
WHERE `entry` = 41836;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Both fragments together will now serve as the key to enter the ruins of the castle. Beware, for you will face both servants of the Legion and cultists of those long forgotten.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The lockbox merely contained the first fragment.'
WHERE `entry` = 41837;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So Blaxbi managed to fulfill his job after all. Excellent. Seeing how youŌĆÖre still in good shape, you may be useful to us - weŌĆÖll see. Take a look around town and see where you can help out. But remember: donŌĆÖt touch ANYTHING!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'And who are you? We donŌĆÖt need bootlickers coming in to waste the bossŌĆÖ time!'
WHERE `entry` = 41838;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'WhatŌĆ”? What is this? Where did youŌĆ”?! No, no, no! Timothy! My little Timmy, no! Oh, Light, why have you forsaken me?! He was just a boy, my sweet, innocent boy!$B$B<Judith is breaking down. Hysteric crying and yelling is all she can do right now. You did what you could. Atleast she has certainty now.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Judith is still sobbing.>$B$BOh, Sara, my darling angelŌĆ” By the Light, please let my Timothy be safeŌĆ”!'
WHERE `entry` = 41840;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Look what the cat dragged in. I was assuming Wordeen had atleast a smidgeon of competency left in his body, but I was sorely mistaken, it seems. To think one of my artifacts escaped those irritating mages and ended up in the clutches of the Shadow Council. Curious, indeedŌĆ”$B$B$N, with the return of the pendant, I am closing the book on this unfortunate circumstance among my subordinates. The traitors have been dealt with, my relics are secured and youŌĆ” You shall be rewarded for delivering a decisive strike against those misusing my possessions.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Speak quickly. I donŌĆÖt intend to waste my time with vermin.'
WHERE `entry` = 41841;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oh, more dusty than my grandmother back in Ironforge. Time has not been kind to this old tome, and the humid air is not exactly helping either. I will seal it properly in my chest and begin analysis back in the SI:7 headquarters. For you, $N, my heartfelt gratitude. Please choose a reward fitting for your service.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Stormwind always envied the Balorians on perfecting the art of successful trade not only with them, but several other nations as well. ItŌĆÖd be a shame if that knowledge would be lost in time, no?'
WHERE `entry` = 41842;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Most impressive. ItŌĆÖs a shame you''re not cut out for this field of work. DonŌĆÖt get me wrong, you possess the skills and wits necessary, but I know your adventurous spirit cannot be tamed and seeks the grandeur of Azeroth. Still, the SI:7 owes you much, so let me reward you appropriately for all youŌĆÖve done.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I am sure you will run into more than enough fitting candidates for my task there.'
WHERE `entry` = 41843;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Wow, what a haul. Might not be exactly what we were supposed to be delivering, but I doubt those greedy bastards in their pirate cove will complain that much. Thank you so much, $N. We owe you big time. You can have this for your troubles, it always gave me the best of luck - the fact IŌĆÖm still here is proof of that.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'YouŌĆÖre tough - or foolish - enough to come to this cursed place on your own, so IŌĆÖm sure youŌĆÖll have no problems going in there and coming back out unharmed - mostly, atleast.'
WHERE `entry` = 41844;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'AhŌĆ” The weight that leaves my very being dissipates as we speak. Being whole once more, passing into the afterlife may not be just a desperate plea anymore. $C, my sincerest thank you. Had it been not for you, I and many others would have been anchored in the world of the living still. My heart rests more easily now, thanks to you. Please, accept one of my remaining physical possessions as a just reward for you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'She is a sadistic creature, torturing souls for her own enjoyment. Her retribution cannot come sooner.'
WHERE `entry` = 41845;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, welcome to Dun Kithas, $N! Truly, it lifts me heart to see new faces in our midst. Dark days are looming over us, no doubt, and every pair of hands shall be vital in the trials ahead.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'A newcomer in Dun Kithas! Welcome, welcome.'
WHERE `entry` = 41846;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Lord Theron has sent you, has he?$B$B<Ranger Faellina peers intently at you>$B$BIf he deems you worthy of this task, then I suppose I need not question his judgment. Very well. Pay close attention, for what I am about to reveal must not be taken lightly. This is no mere errand, and the weight of it should not fall upon ears that do not understand its gravity.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Don''t be shy.'
WHERE `entry` = 41847;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So... the tales whispered by the dwarves of Dun Kithas held truth after all. Curious. One must wonder just how many hidden, long-forgotten passages into Grim Batol yet remain buried beneath stone and time... and what vile things may have once crept forth from their shadows.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be wary. These lands are teeming with Dragonmaw orcs.'
WHERE `entry` = 41848;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You''ve found it... By the Sunwell, I can scarcely believe it.$B$B<Ranger Feallina lifts the crystal, tilting it toward the light. The sun dances across its flawless facets, refracting a cascade of colors.>$B$BThis... this is no mere gem. It is a masterpiece ŌĆö a testament to craftsmanship long thought lost.$B$BYou have our deepest thanks, $C. We will move swiftly now ŌĆö the rangers and I shall descend upon the site and recover as many of these crystals as we can... before reporting back to Lord Theron.$B$BYou have rendered a great service to the Quel''dorei this day, my friend. May the light of the stars guide your path always.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Is there truly no hope left for our kin?'
WHERE `entry` = 41849;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The Gemstone of Naraz... Wait a momentŌĆöthis isn''t right! Look at itŌĆöthis isn''t how it''s meant to be! It''s only half of it, see here? It''s cleanly cut, right along this edge! You didn''t tamper with it, did you?$B$B...No, no, of course not. That cut''s far too precise for anyone without the proper toolsŌĆöor skill, for that matter. Hmm... this complicates things, but don''t start panicking just yet! I''ve an idea where the other half might be.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I must have it!'
WHERE `entry` = 41850;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Hammertoe... attacked by the Dark Irons, you say? Bah, we were rivals more often than not and rarely saw eye to eye, but still, this news sits heavy on me. I can only hope he found a way to escape.$B$BBut there''s no time to dwell on that now! The second half of the GemstoneŌĆöjust as the old texts described! You''ve done well, adventurer, truly well. Thank you, thank you! I''ll take it to Ironforge at once. With the right hands and the right tools, it''ll be restored to its full glory!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Hammertoe probably set up camp close to Angor Fortress. That''s what I would do, at least. The place is well known for its ancient relics.'
WHERE `entry` = 41851;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'While nothing can bring back our fallen brethren, you''ve ensured their sacrifice wasn''t for nothing. These relics you''ve recovered are priceless treasures of knowledge, and they''ll undoubtedly deepen our understanding of the Earthen and our ancestors'' legacy.$B$BOn behalf of the Explorers'' League, I thank you, $C. You''ve done us and our kin a great service.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I beg you, adventurer! Time is of the essence.'
WHERE `entry` = 41852;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Groldan glares at the heads you''ve brought him and spits on the ground.>$B$BHa! That''ll send a clear message to those Shadowforge rats! It''s only a matter of time before word of this reaches their so-called leadership. Let this be a lesson to themŌĆöthink twice before crossing the dwarves of Ironforge, or pay the bloody price!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Vengeance!'
WHERE `entry` = 41853;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ha! Aye, that''s me stash, sure as stone!$B$BThought I''d lost it to those thrice-cursed Dark Irons ŌĆö but seems the sorry louts hadn''t the wit to understand how valuable me notes really are!$B$B<Groldan grumbles as he rummages through the pile, tossing aside old tools and scraps>$B$BNow where''d I put it... Bah, always buryin'' the good stuff under junk... Ah! There it is!$B$BHere ŌĆö take these potions. It''s not much, but it ought to serve ye well out there. Consider it a proper thanks from Groldan Blackforge. Just don''t go wastin'' it on chasin'' rabbits or pokin'' trolls, aye?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it?'
WHERE `entry` = 41854;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'By the Makers, that''s splendid news! With the quarry back in our hands, we''re one step closer to reclaiming the mines and restoring what''s been lost!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I hold no grudge against the Magistrate. I understand that the Dragonmaw threat is more important than the mines.'
WHERE `entry` = 41855;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Amazing work, $R! I''ll send the miners in at once. In just a few days, we''ll be back to mining, and with it, Dun Kithas will see its glory restored once more.$B$BPlease, take this. It''s been in my family for generations, but now... now it''s time for it to taste blood again. You''ve earned it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'We dug too deep... too greedily. Now we''re paying the price for our folly.'
WHERE `entry` = 41856;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah! Now that''s a job well done, $R. I''ll see to it that our fishermen are notifiedŌĆöthe waters should be much safer now, thanks to your efforts.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Where do those murlocs even come from...'
WHERE `entry` = 41857;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The news of the Butcher''s demise brings a certain satisfaction, I''ll admit. Hopefully, that''ll be the last we see of those murlocs. Now, I can finally focus on what truly mattersŌĆöthe war with the Dragonmaw. We''ve got bigger fish to fry.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'And to think that I used to love fish...'
WHERE `entry` = 41858;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Carefully you dig a small hole into the ground. Wrapping the pendant around itself, you lay it softly into the fresh soil, before covering it again in veneration to the dead. For but a moment silence lays upon Elwynn, a warm breeze whispers through the trees and serenity sets in. Performing a last service of respect for Sir Vellas, his parents and Sir Notleigh, you stand in silent contemplation, before continuing on your path.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The grave has long been overgrown, yet the cross is still somewhat intact.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41859;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Moonglade''s tranquility is serene today, don''t you think?',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41860;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Rethevus is breathing heavily. The fight has left him deeply exhausted.>$B$BIncredible! What we heard about you was not an understatement, your mastery over Cenarius'' teachings is as clear as a star-clad sky! Knowing a skilled individual like you to be on our side lets our heart rest easily. We made a promise to you and mother, a promise we shall keep. Here, receive the blessing of the Green Dragonflight. You are more than worthy of it.$B$BFor now, we bid you farewell. Mother awaits us in the Emerald Dream, where the war rages on still. The day when we will see eachother in the verdant expanses cannot come sooner.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Failure is no weakness, but simply a sign of growth waiting to happen.'
WHERE `entry` = 41861;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Another Alliance adventurer, is it?$B$BGood to know Ironforge hasn''t abandoned us completelyŌĆöthough I''d have preferred reinforcements before things reached this sorry state.$B$BAh, don''t mind the grumbling. I''m just an old dwarf with too many battles behind him and not enough warriors at his side.$B$BWe''ve got work to do and Dragonmaw to send back to the dirt. Let''s not waste time.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Aye?'
WHERE `entry` = 41862;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ha! That will make them think twice before showing their ugly faces again.$B$BThis many Dragonmaw lying dead in the dirt should remind them to fear the Wildhammer Clan. With their numbers thinned, our caravans from Dun Kithas might finally get some breathing room.$B$BWell done.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I''ve sent a sizeable patrol to investigate what''s left of Stolgaz Keep... but I haven''t heard a word since.'
WHERE `entry` = 41863;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You''ve done us proud, lad.$B$BTo see this banner againŌĆ” aye, it stirs the heart. The orcs defiled our walls, but they couldn''t claim our spirit.$B$BWith this flying once more above Dun Kithas, our people will remember who we are ŌĆö and what we''re fighting for.$B$BWell done.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I''ll not rest easy until that banner is back where it belongs.'
WHERE `entry` = 41864;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Well done! That''s a fine day''s work ŌĆö the screams of dying Dragonmaw are music to these old ears.$B$BWith their numbers thinned and the keep cleared, we can send a proper unit to reclaim and rebuild. You''ve done more for the Grim Reaches than most ever will.$B$BStolgaz Keep will fly the Wildhammer banner again, and it''s thanks to you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Stolgaz Keep was named after my grandfather. I''ll not see it left to rot under orc boots.'
WHERE `entry` = 41865;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Well done, $C! With these crates in our hands, the Dragonmaw will be scrambling to keep their forces fed and armed.$B$BAnd no one can say Garlin Redbrand didn''t do his part, eh? ŌĆ”Even if I did it through you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be carefulŌĆöGeth''kar is heavily fortified. I''m not joking!'
WHERE `entry` = 41866;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Urgh, that smell could knock out an ogre!$B$B<Dorthas winces and carefully takes the leaking samples from you>$B$BExactly as disgusting as I imagined... but unfortunately, also exactly what I needed.$B$B<He peers closer, his expression shifting from curiosity to concern>$B$BHmm. I was afraid of this. The corruption''s deeper and more complex than I thought. We''re not just dealing with sick wildlifeŌĆösomething bigger is behind all this.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be careful out there. The oozes might not look like much, but they''re not the only twisted things lurking in the dark.'
WHERE `entry` = 41867;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Dorthas squints at the samples, turning them over in his hands. His expression darkens.>$B$BJust as I fearedŌĆ” this isn''t some random corruption. This is the Shadow CurseŌĆöthe same blight Modgud unleashed on Grim Batol during the war.$B$BAnd it''s still active. Even after all these years, the curse is seeping out, spreading past the ruins. Stone can''t hold it back. Time hasn''t weakened it. If no one actsŌĆ” this whole region could fall. This is beyond anything we can handle alone. I''ll send word to the mages in Dalaran. They need to know what''s happening. As for usŌĆ” all we can do now is keep watchŌĆöand pray.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Wish I could go with you, but... well, I learned the hard way I''m better with books than blades.'
WHERE `entry` = 41868;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ha! Now that''s what I''m talkin'' about! You did more with your blade than the whole damn magistrate''s done in years of flappin'' their gums.$B$BYou gave those monsters what they deserved, and maybeŌĆöjust maybeŌĆöwe can walk these roads again without fear.$B$BThank you, friend. My son would''ve been proud.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My lad''s blood cries out for justice. Don''t come back until you''ve made those beasts pay.'
WHERE `entry` = 41869;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Harfig listens closely as you recount the battle. His weathered face softens for the first time. A faint, tired smile creases the edges of his mouth.>$B$BAyeŌĆ” that''s the news I''ve been needing to hear. You gave ''em hell, didn''t you? I can feel it in my chestŌĆölike a weight''s been lifted, if only a little.$B$BI''ll never hold my son againŌĆ” never hear his laugh echo through the hallsŌĆ”$B$BBut thanks to you, some other parent might.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Foul beasts.'
WHERE `entry` = 41870;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, goodŌĆöanother strong back and keen blade.$B$BI hope your travels were light and that you enjoy your stay in Dun Kithas, though there''ll be little rest here, I fear. There''s work to be done, and no time to waste.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome!'
WHERE `entry` = 41871;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Mountaineer Lightboots leans in and sniffs the meat with an almost reverent sigh.>$B$BBy the stones! That smellŌĆ” it''s glorious!$B$BNow where''s that blasted cookpot? We''ll boil some, roast the restŌĆ” or maybe dry it to keep for laterŌĆ” Ah, the possibilities!$B$BYe''ve done more than fill a belly, $R. You''ve helped lift the spirits of a whole outpost. And believe me, that''s worth more than any blade.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I would do anything for a proper feast.'
WHERE `entry` = 41872;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Historian Sternhand reads the journal in silence, flipping the final pages with furrowed brows. He exhales slowly, then closes the book with a firm thump.>$B$BHmm. I suspected something went wrong out there... but not this.$B$BBrangar was once a proud dwarf. A good farmer. It''s a tragedy what happenedŌĆöwhatever did happen.$B$B<He gives you a long look.>$B$BFor the sake of his legacy, I''ll... omit these final entries from the official records. Some things are best left forgotten.$B$BThank you for bringing this to me, $R. You''ve done a service to our history, even if it''s a grim one.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it? You found it at Brangar''s old farmstead?'
WHERE `entry` = 41873;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Sorgan''s eyes widen as he takes the worn tomes into his hands, brushing centuries of dust from the covers.>$B$BBy the MakersŌĆ” I never thought I''d see this again. This oneŌĆöBaggoth''s Testament! It''s a first-hand account of the siege of Firewatch Ridge! Incredible!$B$BYou''ve done more than fetch books, $R. You''ve helped restore the soul of our people. I''ll be poring over these for days.$B$BWho knows what secrets of the past we''ll rediscover?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Did you make it to Stolgaz? Any sign of the archives?'
WHERE `entry` = 41874;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Mountaineer Lightboots taps one of the bricks, nodding in approval.>$B$BSolid stoneŌĆ” good heft to it. These will hold, once the masons get their hands on ŌĆśem.$B$BWell done, $R. You''ve helped hold the lineŌĆöfor now. May the wall stand a little longer thanks to your effort.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'There''s rubble and ruin aplenty out there. We just need to be smart enough to use it.'
WHERE `entry` = 41875;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Magistrate Toughhand strokes his beard and sighs.>$B$BI''m afraid there''s no easy answer. Sal''Galaz mines are overrun with troggsŌĆöfilthy pestsŌĆöand the miners have been driven out.$B$BWithout ore, the forge falls silent. And without the forgeŌĆ” well, let''s just say our mountaineers might be going into battle with rusted blades.$B$BWe''ll have to find a solution. Fast.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You''ve come from Slatebeard''s Forge, have you? I feared this moment would come.'
WHERE `entry` = 41876;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Nazgrim folds his arms and listens intently. After a moment, a smile breaks through his stern expression.>$B$BHurdam ToughhandŌĆ” I haven''t heard that name in some time. A stubborn mule of a dwarfŌĆöbut a loyal one. I owe him more than just words.$B$BAnd besides, the folk of Dun Kithas have held the line longer than any of us expected. If not for their grit, the Dragonmaw would be knocking on Ironforge''s gates by now.$B$BYes. I''ll send word to the guild. You''ll have your ore.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What business brings you from Dun Kithas?'
WHERE `entry` = 41877;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Magistrate Hurdam exhales deeply, shoulders relaxing for the first time in days.>$B$BSo he agreedŌĆ” By the Light, that''s a relief. This will buy us the time we need.$B$BI''ll have couriers ready to receive the first shipment. Slatebeard''s Forge will run hot again, and our defenders will have the steel they need.$B$BYou''ve done more than you know, friend. Dun Kithas is in your debt.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Did you speak to Nazgrim? Please tell me he agreed.'
WHERE `entry` = 41878;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The crystal!$B$B<Grukson turns it over in his hands, clearly impressed.>$B$BIt''s just how I imagined itŌĆöabsolutely perfect. This will make the mace something truly special.$B$BI''d better get to work, then. Maybe this timeŌĆ” my father will finally see what I''m capable of.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you found the crystal yet?'
WHERE `entry` = 41879;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'By the ancestors'' beards, you''ve done what many thought impossible.$B$BWith so many of their officers dead, the Dragonmaw war machine in the Grim Reaches will sputter and die.$B$BCelebrate this victory, but stay sharp ŌĆö the war isn''t over, not yet.$B$BWell done, friend. The mountain remembers.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Zarm''geth is no place for lone wolves. Rally your allies and show those orcs the fury of the Alliance!'
WHERE `entry` = 41880;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Mountaineer Lightboots pries open one of the crates, sifting the grain between his fingers.>$B$BHmmŌĆ” aye, I''ve seen fresher grain in my daysŌĆ” but this isn''t bad. Mold''s only hit a few sacks. With a little work, most of it''s usable.$B$B<He pauses, glancing around, voice dropping to a low whisper.>$B$BStillŌĆ” you saw what that place has become, didn''t you?$B$BGood job, $R. It''s better we have this grain than whatever was lurking there. But if I were youŌĆ” I wouldn''t speak too loudly of what you saw. Some truths are better left buried.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be careful out thereŌĆ”$B$BScouts say Brangar''s Folly is home to darker things now than orcs.'
WHERE `entry` = 41881;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Magistrate Hurdam Toughhand listens intently, clearly impressed>$B$BBy the forge and stone, you''ve done more than I dared hope for! The folk of Dun Kithas and the Grim Reaches owe you a great debt. Take this reward as a token of our thanks.$B$BBut don''t let your guard down yetŌĆöthere''s still Dragonmaw scum skulking in the hills, and we dwarves know better than to trust the peace of a mountain too soon. Stay sharp, and keep your axe ready.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you been any assistance to Steelwind?'
WHERE `entry` = 41882;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Magistrate Hurdam Toughhand inspects the letter with a careful gaze...>$B$BIt would appear that the Dragonmaw Clan is not as united as we once believed. This news is relieving to hear.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it that you bring?'
WHERE `entry` = 41883;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Magistrate Hurdam Toughhand looks on with a slight gaze of disbelief>$B$BYou were successful? By my beard, I cannot believe it!$B$BMany long and hard fought battles will have been avoided thanks to your hard work. The dwarves of Dun Kithas are forever in your favor! Please, take one of these items, as a reward from all of us here.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Preparation will be required if you desire success in the battle to come.'
WHERE `entry` = 41884;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ha! Look at ye, not even half-chewed! That''s a fine bit of croc-clearing you''ve done, friend.$B$BMaybe now I can cast a line without losing a toe. Or a whole leg. Or me sanity!$B$BŌĆ”Actually, forget that last one.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You still alive? Or did the crocs drag you under too?'
WHERE `entry` = 41885;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You actually did it? Thank the ancestors. That should make things safer for nowŌĆöthough I still don''t trust the quiet out here.$B$BAppreciate your help. Not many brave enough to walk into those webs and walk back out again.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Still alive? I meanŌĆöah, back already? No? Then keep your eyes open, and your boots dry...'
WHERE `entry` = 41886;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I must warn you, use this recipe wisely. A misuse of the materials can create the exact opposite of the Concoction of the Emerald Mongoose.$B$BI suggest you follow this recipe closely.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'So, have you made your choice?'
WHERE `entry` = 41887;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You''ve returned ŌĆö and with the Crests of Heroism no less. Your efforts in these treacherous places haven''t gone unnoticed. With each victory, our foothold grows stronger.$B$BThe Alliance thanks you for your bravery.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Hold nothing back. Return with the crests ŌĆö our allies are counting on you.'
WHERE `entry` = 41888;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'These relics speak for themselves. Incindis is no more, and the Sorcerer-Thane''s hand lies still.$B$BThe Firelord will feel this blow and know the Alliance stands ready to snuff out his flames again, if need be. Take this cache, and remain prepared. There may be more lurking in the depths.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The flames are rising. Don''t return empty-handed. Not unless you want to be turned to ash along with them.'
WHERE `entry` = 41889;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'These crests will send a message, loud and clear. You''ve proven your strength once again. We''ll push further with this momentum.$B$BTake your reward, champion. Stay sharp. The war does not rest - and neither do we.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Every moment you delay, our enemies grow more daring. Prove to me the Horde still commands fear. Bring me the crests.'
WHERE `entry` = 41890;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You return bearing the crests of victory. Good. These show the enemy that their darkness cannot withstand our strength. With each blow you strike, you carve the path forward for the Horde.$B$BYour loyalty will not be forgotten.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Horde expects results, not excuses. Tear through the corruption, bring me the crests, and remind our enemies why they fear us.'
WHERE `entry` = 41891;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'These relics speak for themselves. Incindis is no more, and the Sorcerer-Thane''s hand lies still.$B$BThe Firelord will feel this blow and know the Horde stands ready to snuff out his flames again, if need be. Take this cache, and remain prepared. There may be more lurking in the depths.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The flames are rising. Don''t return empty-handed. Not unless you want to be turned to ash along with them.'
WHERE `entry` = 41892;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Sorgan Trustgrip takes his time to inspect the tome, giving it a mighty blow which sends dust about the library haphazardly.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it that you bring?'
WHERE `entry` = 41893;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Would you look at this baby? Chromatic powered turbo charged goodness! This thing will do wonders in getting me back on my feet.$B$BI scrounged up what I could as a reward, it isn''t much, but I hope it''ll work as payment. Now, get lost, I got some tinkerin'' to do.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What can I do for you $C?'
WHERE `entry` = 41894;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Why look at this, such potent ichor! This will surely go a long way to making a few coins. Here, take this cut...this cut.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Psst! You got that ichor?...that ichor?'
WHERE `entry` = 41895;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such magic, foul and intense! This be right what I was lookin'' for. You''ve done well and traveled far. I offer you protection from the shadow, use it wisely and wander safely.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you returned bearing good news, or bad news?'
WHERE `entry` = 41896;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Excellent work. These crests are proof that you''ve broken their lines and shattered their resolve. We''ll use this momentum to press further into their strongholds.$B$BTake this cache and be ready. We may need you again soon.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'We don''t have the luxury of time. Each moment those monsters draw breath, they grow stronger. Show me you''ve stood against them.'
WHERE `entry` = 41897;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It pains me to ask of such things... The Blackroot were once our friends and dearest allies. As much as it hurts to look upon familiar faces and see friends, it is good to know they are now free from the evil that gripped their hearts. You have done the Timbermaw proud, and for that, you shall be rewarded friend.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Has the corruption been rooted out?'
WHERE `entry` = 41898;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'More of the corruption has been cleansed. Each Blackroot that is slain is another step closer to having our race be pure of the vile taint that has cursed us so gravely. The Timbermaw is thankful for your efforts.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'There can be no peace with the Blackroot, they have sought our destruction ever since they have turned to madness. If you wish to get into the good graces of the Timbermaw, perhaps you can fight them on our behalf. Gather ten of the totems they hold sacred, it is how I will track your deeds.'
WHERE `entry` = 41899;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Behold, the creation of my people, the great Sapta of Tranquility. Able to guide ones movements with speed and grace. The very essence of the Timbermaw Sap has been imbued with our strength and given us the boons we have in this world.$B$BYour efforts in helping our tribe have earned you the right to our most traditional Sapta.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You have proven yourself worthy of my attention, and for that, I shall grant you access to my most cherished recipes. Bring me the required materials, and I shall reward you accordingly.'
WHERE `entry` = 41900;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Behold, the creation of my people, the great Sapta of Communion. It can empower ones resistance to the natural world in order to seek guidance. The very essence of the Timbermaw Sap has been imbued with our strength and given us the boons we have in this world.$B$BYour efforts in helping our tribe have earned you the right to our most traditional Sapta.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You have proven yourself worthy of my attention, and for that, I shall grant you access to my most cherished recipes. Bring me the required materials, and I shall reward you accordingly.'
WHERE `entry` = 41901;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Behold, the creation of my people, the great Sapta of Harmony. It can empower and embolden the roots of nature itself. The very essence of the Timbermaw Sap has been imbued with our strength and given us the boons we have in this world.$B$BYour efforts in helping our tribe have earned you the right to our most traditional Sapta.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You have proven yourself worthy of my attention, and for that, I shall grant you access to my most cherished recipes. Bring me the required materials, and I shall reward you accordingly.'
WHERE `entry` = 41902;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Behold, the creation of my people, the great Sapta of Kinship. It can revitalize the most broken of spirits, and raise morale. The very essence of the Timbermaw Sap has been imbued with our strength and given us the boons we have in this world.$B$BYour efforts in helping our tribe have earned you the right to our most traditional Sapta.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You have proven yourself worthy of my attention, and for that, I shall grant you access to my most cherished recipes. Bring me the required materials, and I shall reward you accordingly.'
WHERE `entry` = 41903;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Behold, the creation of my people, the great Sapta of Resilience. It can offer protection against the corruption and poison that dwells deep in the forests. The very essence of the Timbermaw Sap has been imbued with our strength and given us the boons we have in this world.$B$BYour efforts in helping our tribe have earned you the right to our most traditional Sapta.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You have proven yourself worthy of my attention, and for that, I shall grant you access to my most cherished recipes. Bring me the required materials, and I shall reward you accordingly.'
WHERE `entry` = 41904;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You did it! I am relieved to see you safe and sound, as well. With these returned, the group may continue their journey to their new home once more.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Bronzebeard''s hatred towards the Dark Iron is something I couldn''t understand beforehand. Yet witnessing their disregard for morality and life firsthand made me realize where that disdain stems from.'
WHERE `entry` = 41905;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '$N! You''re here! As soon as I saw them return to the lodge, I knew you were successful, yet I still feared for your safety. You have my deepest gratitude. Not only did you risk your life for the innocent, but also braved dangers beyond what the usual adventurer faces.$B$BPlease, have one of these as a token of the good deeds you fulfilled this day.$N!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'This fate was not what we promised them.'
WHERE `entry` = 41906;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah yes, these trinkets have faired well, spared from the flame. I must thank you for all that you have done outsider. Without your help, these surely would have been destroyed. I can only offer you a paltry reward, I just hope it is enough to convey my thanks.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The legacy of my people must be maintained, even if their spirits now walk with the ancestors. Our history can not be lost.'
WHERE `entry` = 41907;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Unrefined and primitive, but undoubtedly potent. $N, your selfless actions of today will not be forgotten. The villagers will hear from this, that I will make sure. Should you find more, do not hesitate to bring them to me.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Our demand for draenethyst remains high. My tribe retains much of its spirituality from Draenor, something we take great pride in. This, however, has its cost. The draenethyst needed for our ancient rituals is scarce and we can barely leave the village without taking heavy risks. It may sound selfish and unsustainable to you, but what are we without our traditions?$B$B$N, the creatures of the coast are drawn to the foreign crystals, not unlike us. Their power is alluring, so like moths drawn to a flame, they gravitate to this tempting energy. For every piece of draenethyst you find, I will tell my people of your deeds, you have my word.'
WHERE `entry` = 41908;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Heghala''s beady eyes widen, if not by much. His agape mouth looks almost terrifying, as he bares his two rows of teeth.>$B$BPoresh Toralar! Blessed be the Twisting Nether! What you have brought us is breathtaking, the proper words to show our gratitude escape me. $N, your name shall be known by every Moro''gai, from this day forward till the end of time.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Large crystal formations are strewn across the coast. Most of their power has already been drained, turning them to nothing more than a beautiful mirror glistening in the rising sun. Yet still, Draenethyst begins to form, in small, glowing clusters all throughout Moonwhisper. They are a rare sight, but all the more powerful in turn.$B$BIf by some miracle you should stumble across these formations and bring them to the village, our people would be immensly indebted to you.'
WHERE `entry` = 41909;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Father sent you? How unlikely of him to relegate a foreigner to me, but truth be told he hasn''t been exactly himself lately. The betrayal is deeply seated, the Elder was a well-loved figure within the tribe, second only to my father. Which is exactly what makes his actions all the more despicable.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome to Moro''gai Village, how can I aid you?'
WHERE `entry` = 41910;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'How barbaric. Tooru, how could you?! He was an aspiring hunter, his heart full of noble aspirations. To Nar''lan, he was like a younger brotherŌĆ”$B$BI had thought after escaping from our dying homeworld, we''d be safe from dangers, atleast for a while. How naive of me, you might say, and you may even be right. Nar''lan knew the risks he''d had to face, as he told me the night he left the village. His resolve was admirable. Today, the Moro''gai have lost a great hunter and an even greater friend.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'We don''t know their motives, and from what Father had told me about their reasons, something isn''t adding up. If they were simply discontent with our way of living, they would not resort to such violence.'
WHERE `entry` = 41911;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'This is sacrilegious! What have they done to this crystal?!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it, Parash''ka? Don''t waste my precious time with your infantile curiosity.'
WHERE `entry` = 41912;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'These will suffice, you have proven your usefulness even as a Parash''ka. The chieftain''s trust in you is more than peculiar, yet I trust his decision nonetheless. Now then, let us uncover what dark magic was cast upon this crystal.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Make haste, young fool. The solution to this enigma cannot be postponed.'
WHERE `entry` = 41913;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The Fallen Ones were enslavedŌĆ” no, they cooperated with the horned fiends you call Satyr? Unbelievable, after all that happened to our people on Draenor, how could Bhu''robi spit on our traditions like that? The elder I know would''ve never let the Draenethyst be defiled by foreign sorcerers. And if what is written in this letter is trueŌĆ” then my Father knows more than he dares to admit.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You''ve been gone for a long time. What could Master Ral''pekta uncover?'
WHERE `entry` = 41914;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'My son has matured a lot in these past years, it seems. Another regrettable thing I have failed to notice. He is becoming a man far sooner than I had given him credit for.$B$BArŌĆÖlia is right. The time of lamentation and idleness is over. We have not survived one genocide to succumb to another conducted by our own kin. Raise your arms, $N. We will silence this false prophet.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The chieftain gazes into the horizon with a melancholic expression.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41915;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I feel an aura of solemnity coming from you. Has it been done? Has this mistake of mine been corrected at last? $C, you have done a great deed for our people. Not only did you save us from damnation, but also showed us that the path we treaded for centuries is one the Moro''gai shouldn''t follow any longer. In a way, Bhu''robi was right, the Draenei need to adapt, to ensure a new future for our people. One free of fear and instead filled with perseverance. If only he hadn''t twisted the meaning of his own belief.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The shadow of fear that Bhu''robi has cast upon our people must stop or else he will be no different than the orcish horde of Draenor.'
WHERE `entry` = 41916;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Bhu''robi might''ve been stopped, but this ordeal is far from over. Like Father said, there are still many of the Fallon Ones out there that are now lost and it is our duty to bring them back into our fold. It is a grueling task and I fear this will not be the last day we lose loved ones, but that is exactly why we have to do everything we can to prevent that from happening. While I am yet inexperienced and in training still, I will support my father and the elders as much as possible.$B$BI have thought long about it, and while I still have much to accomplish here, your actions have instilled a fire in me that I haven''t felt before. For all this time we have secluded ourselves at this coast, we held ourselves back and remained hidden as best we could. But this is not how I wish my life to go. But until I have ensured the security of the village, I cannot leave. So please take this crystal. Should you be in peril, hold it to the sky and I will aid you in battle. You can count on me, $N.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41917;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, the silk I''ve been desperately waiting for. Now that they are in my possession, I can weave them together with these bandages and infuse them with a speck of arcane magic. Our defenders will recover much more quickly now. Has Hara''ne tasked you in retrieving this in her stead? That sly vixen. Don''t get me wrong, she is not unreliable, but more soŌĆ” resourceful. An unusual free spirit among us draenei, her wits and ingenuity are always refreshing and even more surprising at times. I was glad it was her who volunteered to gather the silk for our wounded.$B$BShould you ever return to the southern woods, please stop by her camp. I''d rest more easily knowing someone would check for her well-being from time to time.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Hara''ne has been gone for far too long. Just what is this reckless woman doing?'
WHERE `entry` = 41918;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Hara''ne is a thorough worker. When we still lived on Draenor, she brought all sorts of curious animals and plants to the village, many from which we developed either tasty meals, powerful cures or spiritual incense. I wouldn''t be surprised if she used you as an excuse to explore the woods of this new and strange world and satiate her own curiosity. Please try not to feel disheartened by it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You again? What brings you to me?'
WHERE `entry` = 41919;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Is that Maghan''s cargo? How relieved I am to know he is safe and sound. I hadn''t heard from him in hours and grew concerned about his health and safety. It is shameful to say, but the tribe is not united anymore, and many of our deserted kin have begun acting violently. While we have to protect our lives, they are still old friends and loved ones we had survived the exodus of Draenor with. This whole disaster is just too much to bear and I wish for it to end as soon as possible.$B$BExcuse me, that was uncalled for. Thank you for helping Maghan; and please, make yourself at home.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Greetings, Parash''ka. You look tired from your journeys. This coast is far out in the wilderness, barely do we get visitors besides our local tauren neighbours.'
WHERE `entry` = 41920;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'What are you saying? You have been sent here by another draenei, a riftwalker no less?!',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41921;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A projection crystal... from another draenei?! Please, hand it to me quickly!',
    `RequestItemsText` = '$N, it is good to see you again in the Harborage. How can I assist you?'
WHERE `entry` = 41922;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<A soothing hum emanates from the stone and idol, now synchronized. From high up the ramp, the Dream Portal sends out a wave of energy, followed by a dragonŌĆÖs roar. Whatever you called has now arrivedŌĆ”>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The stone resonates with the idol in your possession. It yearns to be attuned to it, but cannot do so on its own. The closer you come to the mosscovered stone, the clearer are the words that it tries to imprint into your mind: LETHON. Perhaps some dream energy can offer the necessary potency needed.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41923;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<A soothing hum emanates from the stone and idol, now synchronized. From high up the ramp, the Dream Portal sends out a wave of energy, followed by a dragonŌĆÖs roar. Whatever you called has now arrivedŌĆ”>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The stone resonates with the idol in your possession. It yearns to be attuned to it, but cannot do so on its own. The closer you come to the mosscovered stone, the clearer are the words that it tries to imprint into your mind: YSONDRE. Perhaps some dream energy can offer the necessary potency needed.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41924;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<A soothing hum emanates from the stone and idol, now synchronized. From high up the ramp, the Dream Portal sends out a wave of energy, followed by a dragonŌĆÖs roar. Whatever you called has now arrivedŌĆ”>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The stone resonates with the idol in your possession. It yearns to be attuned to it, but cannot do so on its own. The closer you come to the mosscovered stone, the clearer are the words that it tries to imprint into your mind: TAERAR. Perhaps some dream energy can offer the necessary potency needed.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41925;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<A soothing hum emanates from the stone and idol, now synchronized. From high up the ramp, the Dream Portal sends out a wave of energy, followed by a dragonŌĆÖs roar. Whatever you called has now arrivedŌĆ”>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The stone resonates with the idol in your possession. It yearns to be attuned to it, but cannot do so on its own. The closer you come to the mosscovered stone, the clearer are the words that it tries to imprint into your mind: EMERISS. Perhaps some dream energy can offer the necessary potency needed.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41926;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I see you have returned. It is time for this chapter of Karazhan to be closed. The Dark Riders haven taken enough lives during their horrid reign; this will now end. With the whistle destroyed, none may take Lord BlackwaldŌĆÖs place as their next, ultimately dispersing their presence into the winds. Be prepared, $N, I do not know what may happen once I shatter this effigy of malice.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'A riding whistle from Lord Blackwald? So their tyranny has ended. The Dark Riders were once merchants, cursed by Medivh to hunt relics for him till timeŌĆÖs end. It relieves me to see their leader to have been struck down; however, we cannot be sure there are not more of them out in the world, terrorizing the innocent. For now, I can break apart this whistle, but I require additional help for that. Bring me the essences from the undead of this world, and I may be able to crush this foul thing.'
WHERE `entry` = 41927;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The crosses, you have them! Their holy radiance can be felt even from here. $C, it is imperative for us to cleanse this tablet. You may not know it, but these are used by the vile Crypt Lords of the Scourge to command their Nerubian hordes under a tantalizing spell, enhancing their abilities. It must be rid of this world, immediately. Regardless, stay alert. I am certain they will retaliate, as we are destroying one of their precious relics.$B$BBrace yourselves!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'By the Light! What is that decrepit miasma coming from you? $C, whatever you have on you, hand it over, quickly!$B$B<The tablet is given to Tirion, who promptly casts a holy spell on the cobweb-ridden surface.>$B$BIt is as I feared, the protective curse upon this tablet is too strong to be broken. We need to consecrate it with holy might. For that, sacred crosses from the fanatical Scarlet Crusade should be sufficient. These holy relics are not suitable for their sullied hands regardless. $N, deliver them to me as soon as possible!'
WHERE `entry` = 41928;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<You lay everything atop the altar and recite the spell from the grimoire. With each passing word, the air grows heavier and lightning strikes the sky. The mana shard breaks, releasing a strong shockwave. Moments later, a rift opens above it and -┬Ā out of its boundaries - a terrifying nether creature emerges!>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The book you find on the altar has numerous rituals and incantations. One of them, presumably the spell the cultists were currently practicing, speaks of a summoning - the summoning of a dark entity from beyond the Twisting Nether. What is needed is a conduit of great magical properties, as well as some implements. Your thoughts race back to the mana shard. Perhaps this is its true purpose?>'
WHERE `entry` = 41929;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have returned, with KarrshŌĆÖs pendant. His death is regrettable and saddens me deeply. To see a beacon of resilience and strength rot away in such a short amount of time is terrible. Thank you for releasing him of his pain.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It may not have been long since we escaped Timbermaw Hold, but the horrors inside evolve with rapid speed. Who knows what abhorrent creatures you will face inside?'
WHERE `entry` = 41930;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'These totems are worse than I expected. The fumes they release are unbearable and simply touching them leaves burning marks upon my paws. I will have to seal them away before we can deal with them properly.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Unforeseen strength gathered within the Withermaw; their newfound power being too much for their bodies, causing them to tear apart.'
WHERE `entry` = 41931;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I am in awe at the power of these items. With the beastŌĆÖs heart, we will break the foul barrier around the totems. GrammonŌĆÖs tongue will let them speak true and the waters of purification will wash away all impurities.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My seal will not hold for long, $N. Please hasten your efforts.'
WHERE `entry` = 41932;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'What a hideous creation. Further proof that the life inside our great sanctum is rotting by the minute. Yet still, it serves a purpose. It shall pave the way for the Timbermaw to reclaim what has been torn from us by cruel malefactors. Now I can concoct a salve powerful enough to cleanse our sacred totems.$B$B$N, this humble coven expresses its gratitude towards you. Through your courage, we have made the first step in purifying Timbermaw Hold. Take this essence and use it on your delves into this den of evil. With enough of it, you may break the barrier inside and finally come to the root of it all.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Timbermaw Village will be heavily guarded. Be best prepared, for the Withermaw have abandoned all morality.'
WHERE `entry` = 41933;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'In our ancient teachings, there is a legend that connects all furbolg tribes. It speaks of our creation, as it is said the twin gods have brought us into the world as it was still young. As juvenile cubs they frolicked through the untouched wilds of Kalimdor, rolling around in the dewladen grass of the early mornings. Laughter filled the air and their unbound energy floated all around them. Bursting with their power, the droplets of the wet grass fell onto the roots of gigantic trees, seeping through the bark and becoming one with the land. Over time, these droplets grew and took the semblance of the young ursine gods.$B$BTo us furbolgs there is nothing more important than aiding our progenitors in protecting the wild. Seeing Ursol die for a second time fills my heart with anguish and pain, a being as noble as him did not deserve this fate. $N, the Timbermaw are forever in your debt. Please take this powerful salve and cleanse the remaining corruption in Timbermaw Hold.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<Narkogg is stuck in a praying position. Through the rough whispers of his maw you can deduce him singing a ritualistic song.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41934;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<With the essences at hand, you read the runes out aloud. Benevolent rays of warmth encompass the spirit of Azuregos, before his corporeal body begins manifesting on the leaf laced ground. After finishing the incantation, the mighty dragon bellows a mighty roar.>$B$BWhat a gullible fool you are. Did you really expect me to hand a mere mortal the powerful treasures of my flight? Ridiculous! My treasures are mine and mine alone. As reward for your naivete, let me demonstrate how hospitable the Blue Dragonflight can be!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it, mortal? What desire drives you to pester me in my ghostly state, peacefully roaming these lands? Spare it, I know the answer already; riches and baubles are the foolŌĆÖs only errand. You are too late then, I can and will not assist you in your absurd quest for treasure. How is a ghost supposed to do that, idiot?$B$B<You tell the dragon spirit about the relic you possess.>$B$BOh, a relic of resurrection, you say? Perhaps you arenŌĆÖt such a simpleton after all. Listen carefully, mortal! I wonŌĆÖt repeat myself twice. I am offering you a deal: Resurrect me with that artifact and the riches you so desperately seek shall be yours. Gather the essence of my lesser brethren, the greater good demands their noble sacrifice. It may be grand, but it is a sacrifice I am willing to make. Only then will you be able to invoke the scrollŌĆÖs latent power.'
WHERE `entry` = 41935;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'This fragranceŌĆ” Pure, unadulterated energy lies within these vials. Whatever will be brought into this world through the crystal''s rift will be, without a doubt, a demon of insurmountable power. $N, ready your allies and yourself; this will not be an easy task. Brace yourself!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What brings you here, $R? I seeŌĆ” The aura you exude paints a clear picture. You possess something extraordinary, do you not?$B$B<You present the crystal with Daio. His eyes widen at the sight of it.>$B$BBy the Great Beyond! Never have I laid my eyes upon such an immaculate rift crystal before. $N, can you even fathom what you are holding in the palm of your hand? With a rift crystal of such magnitude, who knows what powerful demon I could summonŌĆ” $C, listen closely, the blood of mighty demons is drenched in nether energy. Bring me ten vials of their blood. The strongest fiends roaming the Tainted Scar, the Darkwhisper Gorge and the mountaintops of Hyjal are ladden with such energies. With it, we may open a rift powerful enough to lure in a demon beaming with power for the taking!'
WHERE `entry` = 41936;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Presenting the honorable spirit with the pendant, a shiver of awe travels down your spine. Silence falls over Moonglade and your surroundings dim as your focus on the ursine figure before you grows stronger. In that moment, a familiar voice rings inside your head:$B$BThank you for saving my brother. The elders of the wild offer you this in return.$B$BAt the paws of the great spirit lay trinkets, presumingly the reward for releasing Ursol from his pain. Choose wisely.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The great spirit looks at you with a venerable gaze.>'
WHERE `entry` = 41937;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'This writing is in Kalimag, the language of the elements. Not many know of this language, let alone speak or read it. It is good you came to me, as I can indeed read a few words on it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What can I help you with?'
WHERE `entry` = 41938;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Vortalus, you say? Worrisome to see elementals making a pact in such large numbers with the mortal races. Especially after what had happened here, at the Earthen Ring. This begs another question, however. What do the elements expect of such a coalition? Were they servants of the Blackwind tribe or was it the other way around? If the wind lords are bringing other forces under their fold, then they must be preparing for something greater.$B$B$N, thank you for your courage. YouŌĆÖve done something incredible today and shown your potential as an aspiring shaman of our order. The others are surely expecting more great things from you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Our Far Seers and speakers are concerned about the elemental unrest boiling all around us. Even the trainees and initiates feel that uneasiness. All the more reason to get to the bottom of this.'
WHERE `entry` = 41939;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Great work, young one. My intuition proved correct - these cores harbor sinister energy within, bubbling and brewing with anger. With their essence still bound to the core, I can calm their minds and release them from their pain. They will return to their elemental planes and, given time, awaken once more in Azeroth. With a renewed purpose and cleansed spirit. Take one of these gifts as compensation for your selfless act to nature. Please, donŌĆÖt hesitate.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The brute force of the elements can be overwhelming. Stay concentrated and focused on your spirit within, then you''ll have nothing to fear.'
WHERE `entry` = 41940;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The fragrance of life courses through this earth. With it, an abundance of life can be fostered, perhaps even restore what was thought of to be lost forever. Bewali did well in tasking you with recovering this soil.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Greetings, brave traveler. What brings you to these ailed lands?'
WHERE `entry` = 41941;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Although there is no life left within these bones, the spores keep trying to search for nutrients, like a writhing parasite searching for prey. This is not a natural occurrence, yet it is not purely magical either. At this point it is a wholly new amalgamation of forces, and it wonŌĆÖt be easy to eradicate it.$B$BThe plan we have come up with is simple in concept. We will plant this tree sapling in the enriched earth you have brought us. Afterwards, we will apply the spores to the tree and observe what will happen. In our previous observations with saplings planted in plagued earth, they withered away in minutes, leaving a mutated husk behind. We assume the elementally enriched earth will protect the tree against the aggressors and allow it to grow freely. It will take a while, so if you ever come by again, maybe you are lucky enough to witness it.$B$BEither way, I must give my thanks to you, and Bewali as well. Every step taken brings us closer to healing these lands for good.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Once we have the missing items, Rayne and I will have all we need to conduct our research on a more practical level.'
WHERE `entry` = 41942;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The elements have spoken of your return, $N. It will take time before the waters are pure again. But with no further corruption being funneled into Maraudon anymore, nature can do so in serenity and peace.$B$BTake this for your deeds in restoring balance to Azeroth.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Satyrs are a plague upon Azeroth. Their machinations for their dark lords have disrupted the balance numerous times.'
WHERE `entry` = 41943;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Meat! And heaps of it, too! ParashŌĆÖka, who set you up for this? Or did you do it on your own volition? Either way, it hardly matters to me. With a supply like this, our defenders will have the strength to repel those heretics for days to come! A reward is needed for your actions. Here, a traditional draeneic recipe, altered to fit the cuisine of this new world.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Denphar struggles with his farm and F''eesh couldn''t reel in a fish for two days now! If this continues, we wonŌĆÖt be able to defend ourselves anymore...'
WHERE `entry` = 41944;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Hm, I am surprised. You listened well and brought exemplary brains. The way their juices are dripping on the floorŌĆ”$B$B<Fena MaŌĆÖdar is salivating at the sight of the grey matter inside your hands. With a swift movement, she snatches them out of your hand and starts chomping on them. Liquid, blood and bits fall to the floor.>$B$BI canŌĆÖt get enough of this savoury taste, the slick surface, the gooey texture! It is simply wonderful! You remedied your mistake, young one. Atleast you are responsible when it comes to consequences caused by your actions. Either way, donŌĆÖt cause any more ruckus around here!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What are you gawking at me like that? Move!'
WHERE `entry` = 41945;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'That was a close one. Let us hope this will teach them to not come here again. I thank you endlessly for saving my life and my dear farm. You see, the earth on this coast has unique properties that make it difficult to grow crops. On top of it, the flora of your world is still difficult for me to fully grasp, even after all the time we have been here. Still, I want to reward you for your good deed. Take it, they are homegrown!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'TheyŌĆÖre still coming!'
WHERE `entry` = 41946;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So the wretch has met its end? Excellent. Twenty three of our people did this monster maul during his last rampage. With him gone, we can rest a bit more easily now.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I have to coordinate the defenders, so be quick about your business.'
WHERE `entry` = 41947;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, the nuisance of the south has been dealt with. These bearfolk elude me. Not long ago, they kept to themselves, barely engaging with the village, until they started acting violent and aggressive. It happened roughly around the same time that traitor BhuŌĆÖrobi left the village. I hope there is no connection between the twoŌĆ”',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What is it?'
WHERE `entry` = 41948;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Excellent display, ParashŌĆÖka. You are a true ally to the draenei, the real draenei. DonŌĆÖt celebrate too soon, however. There is still much to be done.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I want their blood to paint this coast dark red.'
WHERE `entry` = 41949;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'More of those despicable crystals. I feel such anger inside me laying eyes upon this defilement of our sacred draenethyst. Tainted, broken and sullied. Whatever theyŌĆÖve done with it is unforgivable!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You are back, did you find something in that red canyon?'
WHERE `entry` = 41950;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It is true that I know a bit more about these crates, but it has been quite some time since I last saw them in person.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It is not safe out here. If youŌĆÖre not familiar with these woods, I suggest you seek shelter at our village to the north.'
WHERE `entry` = 41951;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So it was the bearfolk who were acting as laymen between the hoofed fiends and the Fallen Ones. You are saying they tried delivering the crystals to the large cave up the hills towards the auburn cliffs? I have heard the network of tunnels beneath the mountain is their sacred hideout. A foreboding prospect.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'If there are more than two parties involved in BhuŌĆÖrobiŌĆÖs scheme, then what does that tell us about his allegiances - and moreover, his aspirations?'
WHERE `entry` = 41952;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The horned fiend; this satyr Selenaxx, you say? He absorbed the energy from the geode and infused his body with it, becoming one with the draenethyst?! To witness such blasphemy even in this new world. $C, the power of draenethyst is deeply alluring and requires immense willpower to not succumb to once tapped into its pulsing energy. There areŌĆ” stories of Draenei falling victim to their draenethyst addiction and eventually crystalizing, ultimately becoming draenethyst themselves. Thus they return to Draenor and enter the cycle of its lifeblood.$B$BFor now, I will have to prepare the cleansing ritual for the geode shards you brought. It will take time and effort, but I and moreover the MoroŌĆÖgai are deeply indebted to you. Your continued support to our tribeŌĆÖs survival shall not go unrewarded. Please choose one of these bracelets, so that they may protect you against the evils yet to come.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'We know little about the bearfolk, they kept to themselves most of the time. For what reason we can only speculate. Was it always their goal to conspire against the MoroŌĆÖgai? Is the DraenethystŌĆÖs power really all they are after?'
WHERE `entry` = 41953;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Fine pieces indeed. The elements of this world saturate the leather, their surface brimming with vibrant energy, elevating those who wear them into combat. Your expertise in the art of leatherworking proved to me that you are worthy of my teachings. Beforehand, a lecture and second trial await you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Show me what wonders your kin is capable of.'
WHERE `entry` = 41954;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Shimmering scales, robust leather and a silky smooth texture. These hydra remind me of our own wildlife, an ancient time ago when Draenor was still blessed with beasts to hunt. I still remember a long hunt for an elusive specimen of a species we called RholuŌĆÖban, ShadowŌĆÖs Trail in your tongue. We followed the two-headed beast for ten nights, before encountering it in a clearing. It mauled three of our hunters, before Fan DheŌĆÖra and I felled the beast, returning home with its pristine fur. The chieftain should still possess the cloak I crafted from that hide.$B$BExcellent skinning, ParashŌĆÖka. Your mastery of the leatherworking craft is no laughing matter, after all. As promised, I will teach you how to harness the power of the hydra and infuse it with the elements of your world. Speak to me again to begin your lesson.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not underestimate them. A masterful craftsman procures their materials alone, so be prepared for their mighty fury.'
WHERE `entry` = 41955;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The Greenpaw are beyond salvation? And our brothersŌĆÖ enclave fights to free the Winterfall tribe from their dark shackles? Time is truy running out. We have to make haste and reconcile with the other Timbermaw as quickly as possible.$B$B$N, thank you for showing us this ray of hope. I will hold a discussion with the others and hopefully send a small envoy to our brothers and sisters up north soon. They shall not be left alone in this everlasting night.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Us Furbolg once roamed the enchanted forests of Kalimdor, tending to the wildlife and flora and maintaining their balance. But since the LegionŌĆÖs second invasion, almost all of our brethren heed to call of darkness that those demons have left festering on our sacred Land of Stars.'
WHERE `entry` = 41956;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It has been long, $N. We have heard of your exploits inside Timbermaw Hold and are showing eternal gratitude for the sacrifices you have made for our people. What you accomplished is not a natural given, others would have not shown such compassion to a race that isnt their own. Now tell me, what brings you to me?',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41957;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Here you are, as expected. Fate is a force beyond our grasp, and if you try to deny your actions are not defined by fate, then I fear you still have much to learn, mortal.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41958;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Does Itharius miss me so much? I am almost moved to tears. What has changed that the old fool willingly sents mortals to my lair? Let us hope his mother doesnŌĆÖt hear of this.$B$B<InsomŌĆÖni breaks out into hysterical laughter.>',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 41959;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Laughter echoes through the cave. Like a hyena, InsomŌĆÖni cackles at the sight of JamŌĆÖwahliŌĆÖs tusks in an unnatural manner.>$B$BWhat goes around comes around, JamŌĆÖwahli. You thought your life would be spared under the false protection of your Blood God, but you miscalculated. Nothing compares to my unrivaled cunning, traitor. This is what awaits all who dare defy my absolute rule.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The fool shall bleed for his arrogance. I want you to make sure of that.'
WHERE `entry` = 41960;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The myths were true. Such a powerful relic, thought to be lost in time. With it in my hand, IŌĆ” I am certain we can discover what evil is behind all this misery befalling my people. $N, thank you for your continued help, but donŌĆÖt rest yet. We still have much to do.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I have waited for your timely return. Tell me, has the Green Dragonflight been able to aid you in your quest?'
WHERE `entry` = 41961;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The conversation ends and Fangorn returns back to his eternal vigil.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The ancient does not move. Like an immovable object, he just stares into the horizon.'
WHERE `entry` = 41962;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good work. Now that everything is gathered, I can extract a blessing from the acorn that will have you understand the words of nature itself. Be wary, however. The spell wonŌĆÖt last forever, so hurry to Fangorn with a steady pace.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Greetings, $N. I see your quest is urgent. Fangorn was an ally of our people during the War of the Ancients, his powerful magic and wisdom were key in securing victory over the highborne traitors. Following the Sundering, he remained dormant on the island of Kalidar until this day, influencing the world around him ever so vigilantly.$B$BThe furbolg was correct, he speaks a long forgotten language. One that even the druids of Moonglade barely speak anymore. Teaching it to you would take years, but I can help you in understanding it, even if for a little while. From the foot of the World Tree, bring me an Acorn of Nordrassil, sap from the Shrine of Aessina in Ashenvale and five Elixirs of Dream Vision. Bring me these ingredients and you may progress on your quest with my assistance.'
WHERE `entry` = 41963;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Gorn trembles at the news you bring him. An angered growl bares his sharp fangs as he tries to compose himself.>$B$BPerothŌĆÖarn. Second hand of Xavius, the Satyr Lord. There is no mistaking it. This horn fragment and the Withermaw totems share the same kind of malignant energy. A vile mixture of demonic essences andŌĆ” an unknown dread. Such a crushing presence, it is incredibly profane to even look at.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome back, $N. Did you have any success with old Fangorn?'
WHERE `entry` = 41964;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Marvelous! The purest of blazes, a primordial heartbeat resonates within this inconspicuous ball of flame. No evil in this world or any other can hide from its revealing light.$B$B$N, it is time. We will erase the darkness from within Timbermaw Hold once and for all.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Please remain cautious. The Molten Core is a treacherous place, and your allies cannot be prepared enough for the dangers inside.'
WHERE `entry` = 41965;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<A torn look spreads across NarkoggŌĆÖs face. At first you cannot discern it properly, but the wailing and sobbing coming from him affirm your suspicion: He is crying.>$B$BAfter all these years of suffering and torment, my people can finally release a sigh of relief. The corruption befalling most of our kind and one of our sacred gods has finally been quelled. All thanks to the valiant efforts of brave protectors like you. My words cannot properly convey the gratitude we have towards you and your kin. You will forever be welcome with the Timbermaw, as the cherished hero of the Furbolg.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You are back! Tell me, quickly! Were our plans successful? Are my people finally free?'
WHERE `entry` = 41966;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Brolan Windhorn lets out a deep sigh of relief.>$B$BYou have saved me much turmoil, now that I know I can sleep more at peace. You have done the Windhorn a great service this day, and I offer you a token of our appreciation outsider.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Our numbers have already been thinned, I must ensure that not one more of our already beleaguered kin is brought to an untimely death.'
WHERE `entry` = 41967;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Bulrok Cloudhoof takes his time inspecting the horns, tapping his finger upon the surface of the bone with curiosity.>$B$BI believe this is what I am looking for, you have done well.$B$B<The arrogant tauren lets a smirk cross his face.>$B$BHere, take this as a token of thanks from the Cloudhoof tribe.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I am not looking to waste my time, if you cannot procure the horns, I will find another who can.'
WHERE `entry` = 41968;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Such a marvelous material, so bright, and colorful! This will do wonders for the coming ceremonies, and will certainly be better than the last raiment.$B$BThank you $C, and please, take this as a reward.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Has the fur been procured?'
WHERE `entry` = 41969;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So, it is as I feared...$B$B<Torgan the Wise takes a moment, his face filled with sorrow, and dread.>$B$BMay their spirits pass peacefully to their ancestors. I do hope they met a quick, and merciful end. These poor individuals were only travelling here to celebrate, and now have only found brutality.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do you bring news? Be it good or bad?'
WHERE `entry` = 41970;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Brave Wildheart inspects the letter, opening it, before gazing it over with a curious tone, the building rage and displeasure can be seen upon his features, all before a heavy snort could be heard.>$B$BThat road has always been dangerous, but for such violence? I will be sure to speak with Elder Moonhoof himself. This matter will need to be investigated further, for we do not know who the real attacker is. The Draenei have never been so overtly aggressive.$B$BI will be sure to have any others travelling to the refuge be under the supervision and escort of our defenders.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How can I help you?'
WHERE `entry` = 41972;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Gordnak inspects the letter, a smile crossing his face.>$B$BZalwan huh? Been a few months since I heard from him, shocked he''s still alive with all that stuff going on in Tel''Abim, no wonder he wants out.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Is there something you need?'
WHERE `entry` = 41973;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Gordnak takes his time to inspect the scale, watching it glimmer in the light, and radiate with magical energy.>$B$BIt would appear this is what I have come for. You have done well, here, take this coin, and a reward on my behalf.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I would advise caution, the large behemoths carry immeasurable strength.'
WHERE `entry` = 41974;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ahh, bout time! I knew I could count on that big lunk of a tauren! Oh, and count on you, of course!$B$BNow all I need to do is wait a few days and kick this stinkhole, you''ve done me a huge solid kid. This money is going to buy me a whole new life. A life away from water pumps and blistering fingers. Take it easy!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Back so soon are you?'
WHERE `entry` = 41975;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Magnificent, I was once as ignorant to think the Tauren had no history, and just wandered plains like nomads. This certainly has changed my view upon them as a whole.$B$BYou have done well adventurer, please, take this coin for doing such brave, and noble work.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Remember, the Canyon is located deep within Thousand Needles, you will need to travel to the far corners of Kalimdor to find it.'
WHERE `entry` = 41976;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I spent the entirety of my youth surrounded by such relics. The craftsmanship of the Windhorn is certainly superb.$B$BWithout your help, this history would have been lost to time. I thank you, for everything that you have done this day.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Tread carefully, the Grimtotem have fortified Windhorn Canyon and claimed it as their own. The large, steep cliffs provide an excellent redoubt for defence. I advise you to bring allies if you wish to help.'
WHERE `entry` = 41977;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Blood for blood. You have done well, and repaid this evil with vengeance. I hope you feel the satisfaction that I feel, for I am vindicated, even if anger still burns deep in my heart.$B$BI must thank you for being the hand of my wrath. Please, take these coins, as tribute from me, and those lost.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It is only a matter of time before they feel what I have felt. They shall pay for their actions, and I shall have my revenge.'
WHERE `entry` = 41978;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Cairne takes the letter, gazing it over with a stern, an serious gaze.>$B$BLonghorn was right to send you, this matter could bring dire consequence.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What brings you to Thunderbluff?'
WHERE `entry` = 41979;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A letter, from Cairne?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What business do you have?'
WHERE `entry` = 41980;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Cairne takes a moment to process the information, his hand rubbing against his jaw.>$B$BWindhorn Canyon. I did hear about trouble there from the Windhorn Tribe who were expelled.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 41981;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Cairne gazes upon you with a look of approval.>$B$BYou have done well, and have brought peace to the Tauren. The Deathtotem shall trouble us no longer young blood. Please, be bestowed by an item that shall bring you fortune in the days to come.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Take heart, and be careful in your task. I am certain that the Deathtotem are aided by dark magic. Bring what company you can, and be swift in your actions.'
WHERE `entry` = 41982;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Is that IqaŌĆÖquluk?! Never would I have thought that a stranger would be the one to fish the great Moonfish. I can just imagine the look on PanukukiŌĆÖs face when he hears about this, how amusing!$B$B$N, you truly made my day, perhaps even my whole week with your visit. I want to reward you with a prized secret of mine. Since you are an avid fisher, let me show you how to craft your own fishing pack, the perfect companion for those very long days out on the ocean. A staple in Tuskarr culture!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Coming back for more stories?'
WHERE `entry` = 41983;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Now thatŌĆÖs what I call proper equipment. Thanks a bunch, friend. Now I can enjoy some time off and do the same thing IŌĆÖve been doing the last 30 years - just at a different place.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I donŌĆÖt really care where you get the stuff from, just make sure they donŌĆÖt break apart if I reel in the big ones!'
WHERE `entry` = 41984;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Look at that beauty! Sleek design, a wonderful black finish on top and most of all - it wonŌĆÖt explode in my face when I turn it on. Thanks a lot, $N. Now there should be nothing standing in my way to properly prepare NoggenfoggerŌĆÖs banquet.$B$BHere, you can have a copy of the cookerŌĆÖs blueprints for coming in clutch there. Thanks again, kid!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do you have the cooker?!'
WHERE `entry` = 41985;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Those were incredible. You really got a hand for cooking, Dirge has to watch out youŌĆÖre not dethroning him too soon if those are any indication of your culinary skills. Either way, here is the finished cooker. Bring it to Dirge and tell him he can come back anytime, if his pride as a goblin allows it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Dirge is demanding his cooker to be finished immediately? This goblin got some nerve. Coming to me in the first place was a surprise, but then again, gnomish engineering is simply superior to the childish attempts at creating machines these green amateurs are demonstrating. Dirge must have realized it himself eventually. You want to know why? Ask him why he only has three fingers left. There were others before me building his cooker for him, letŌĆÖs just say that.$B$BRegardless, if he wants it to be done, I need fuel. And I donŌĆÖt mean crude things like oil or whatnot. No, I require brain fuel in the form of food! My synapses demand the delectable taste of Monster Omelet, a delicacy made from Giant Eggs. Bring me ten and I will finalize his cooker in no time.'
WHERE `entry` = 41986;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A chaotic miasma stirs within them. It will take some time to restore balance to them. Should you acquire more, do not hesitate bringing them to me.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The elements are abstract things and can take many forms. Natural like the earth beneath our hooves or the clear water flowing downstream; or even more tangibly dangerous things like manifestations of pure elemental energy. Those incarnations are guests, if you will, from their respective elemental planes and need an anchor in this world to act. Bound by their shackles, they are tethered to Azeroth by the cores within the corporeal forms built from raging elemental power.$B$BThe rampaging elementals need to return to their elemental planes in a tranquil state; a task we can accomplish by calming the unrest within those cores. Bring them to me and the Earthen Ring will be in your favor.'
WHERE `entry` = 41987;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Greetings, what a surprise seeing a member of the Horde here. Did Tohnizte send you? I guess her worriful nature is a blessing in disguise, I could actually use your help.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Are you here to help?'
WHERE `entry` = 41988;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have it! ButŌĆ” It appears to be damaged. How unfortunate, but probably for the best. This way, it cannot be misused for heinous acts of those wishing discord upon this world. I will return to the Earthen Ring with this now safely in my care. Thank you again, $N. Without your help, the naga may have seized it for themselves. Please, take this as a gift from the Earthen Ring.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'It is said the Idol of Neptulon possesses immense power over the element of water, allowing its user to summon whirlpools, rising tides and other dangerous phenomena. We cannot allow it to fall into the hands of evil.'
WHERE `entry` = 41989;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Is it done? Great, now letŌĆÖs not waste any more time here. IŌĆÖll secure the relics and meet up with Richard back in MoroŌĆÖgai Village. Thank you again for your help, stranger. I appreciate it. Here, you can keep one of the treasures for yourself, as a token of appreciation by me.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I know this is disgraceful, but I just canŌĆÖt help it.'
WHERE `entry` = 41990;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Kralt lets out a huff of breath, a sigh of relief, his features easing from their aged stress.>$B$BYou have eased my burdens outsider, and for that I must thank you. My stockpile grows for the coming hibernation.$B$BPlease, take this, as a sign to show you not all furbolg are lost in rage.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'So many things to do. Time always marching on.'
WHERE `entry` = 41991;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Even after being recovered, the youngest sibling was placed last. This is merely the outcome of one far too zealous to seek anything other than the Sun.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Speak no word of this to any villager. We must not incur the ElderŌĆÖs attention.'
WHERE `entry` = 41992;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Pride and hatred blinded them into cunning yet mischievous powers. They chose to embrace young LoŌĆÖshoŌĆÖs darker side. An appealing thing the rebellious sibling may be when the world itself seems against you.$B$BThe flow is shifting. Warmth makes my fur tingle. AnŌĆÖshe is with us once more.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'His silence is deafening.'
WHERE `entry` = 41993;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It is done then. A grim day, but it does not matter. AnŌĆÖsheŌĆÖs warmth will embrace me come dawn.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The ancestors must be allowed to rest.'
WHERE `entry` = 41994;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You pay blood with more bloodshed. Do not think this absolves you of your actions. But you at least had the conviction to right your wrong.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My words and anger are wasted on you, murderer.'
WHERE `entry` = 41995;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So you managed to cull some of their numbers. Well, better than nothing. Worst comes to shove, I will just shove some silk in my ears..',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My eyes are growing weary.'
WHERE `entry` = 41996;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, I will take this to Innkeeper Warmbreeze. He has the perfect kimchi recipe for this meat, and I bet he still keeps some of that stiff drink his night elven friends gave alongside the recipe.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'My expectations are high; do not fail me, adventurer.'
WHERE `entry` = 41997;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'What a beautiful blue, to be expected, I suppose. This whole area seems to favor this color.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Before you return, I will have some of my tools ready, alongside some concoctions to test against the crystal.'
WHERE `entry` = 41998;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'While I cannot provide you with new clothing just yet, you may choose from these I crafted from the last batch I had.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I wonder what I should tailor first.'
WHERE `entry` = 41999;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I sense some tranquility to the south; your task was indeed a success.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You would be doing a kind favor.'
WHERE `entry` = 42000;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Stand back while I dabble in forces you cannot even begin to imagine.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not underestimate the furbolgs.'
WHERE `entry` = 42001;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The shimmering blade reflects the scorching sun in an unnatural light. Getting closer, the parasite inside your hand almost tears off your forearm with the force it is pulling itself towards the sword. You can feel the heated metal on your skin and it sizzles as the tentacles cause your hand to grasp the handle. Screaming and against all the pain, you pull the blade outside the sand. Soon the pain is gone and the weapon rests in your hand.$B$BŌĆ£You have played this part well, insect. Yet there is still much to be done.ŌĆØ',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The ages have not touched this sword.'
WHERE `entry` = 42002;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'With the reagents at hand, the voice speaks to you yet again. You have grown accustomed to the pain inflicted when that happens:$B$BŌĆ£How does it feel, servant? The pressure. The darkness. The comforting embrace of an endless chasm. There are truths and power resting deep beneath the mantle of shadows cast above the vast abyss. Waiting to be discovered, waiting to burst forth into your unknowing world.$B$BNow, take the nail and carve the bladeŌĆÖs name into the ageless metal: ThilŌĆÖphoral.ŌĆØ',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The altar lies abandoned, lost to the depth of the Great Sea.'
WHERE `entry` = 42003;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You present the four enormous hearts on the altar, before driving the blade through all of them. Blood squirts out and quickly disperses in the salty ocean water for just a moment. Soon after does the green sludge that is the dragonŌĆÖs blood run along the runes you carved inside the swordŌĆÖs metal - until it seeps into it, giving the runes a sickly purple glow. Next, the hearts begin contorting and assimilating themselves into ThilŌĆÖphoral, leaving nothing but the pulsating weapon behind.$B$BŌĆ£We are almost there.ŌĆØ',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The altar draws you in, even more than before.'
WHERE `entry` = 42004;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'ThilŌĆÖphoral in one hand, the splinter in the other. Reluctantly you place the splinter into the indentation on the swordŌĆÖs surface. Almost immediately, the small piece of wood begins taking root inside the blade, which prompts the vine before you to reach out for ThilŌĆÖphoral. Slithering along your forearm, it pulls you closer, while also grasping at the hand harboring the parasite. Now violently, the vine strangles your hands together under an incredible force while emitting a ghastly purple fume. You can feel the tendrils of the parasite retreating from your brain, through your arm, out of your hand.$B$BThe ordeal does not last much longer, the vine loosens its grip eventually and in your now freed hand lies ThilŌĆÖphoral, merged with the parasite in an unnatural magenta light. Just as the voice inside your hand foretold: it fulfilled its path. Thanks to you. Because of your actions, it will now observe and proclaim its discoveries. To whatever force had brought it into this world.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '<The vine is pulsating in an irregular rhythm. Its abhorrent appearance looks out of place in the dreamscape.>'
WHERE `entry` = 42005;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The icy cold of the cave has preserved EvenpikeŌĆÖs body and halted decomposition. You were sadly too late.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42006;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'By the Makers, he was right. Oh, Odum, you lunatic! Betting your life on it was not worth it!$B$B<Brohann exhales a deep sigh of exhaustion.>$B$B$N, my friend was searching for an old relic he presumed to be of Titan origin, the celestial beings that once visited Azeroth. Many scholars and professors in our great city of Ironforge theorize a link between the dwarvesŌĆÖ creation and those god-like beings. He assumed what you now hold in your hand could bring dwarvenkind one step closer to the truth, but it appears to not be complete. Still, Evenpike paid with his life to bring us this phenomenal find and I will honor his sacrifice with pride. Once I am done here in Stormwind, I will present it to High Explorer Magellas in the Great Library of Ironforge for further research.$B$BFor you, I have a just reward, for both your heroism and contribution to archeology. May you fare well on your journeys, traveler.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '$N! You have returned. Pray tell, where is Evenpike?'
WHERE `entry` = 42007;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The rumors were correct, rarely have I seen such a smooth and silky pelt before. I cannot wait to start working with it. As promised, a reward for you as well. I am sure you will find ample use for it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Make haste, $C. My liege is not known for his patience.'
WHERE `entry` = 42008;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A harrowed deed has been done. LoktanagŌĆÖs body will decompose, become one with the earth again. I know what you have done lies heavy on our hearts, but it was necessary. With time, they will emerge again and foster the growth of nature once more.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I cannot tell what lies before you on your journey inside Timbermaw Hold. The spirits do not dare speak of that place and deny me any wisdom.'
WHERE `entry` = 42009;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It may look like they were buried for eons, but donŌĆÖt be fooled. The waters within have a magical property which causes them to rise upwards to the surface, so that they may embrace the moonŌĆÖs light once more. With WinterspringŌĆÖs heavy snow however, they never could emerge truly. In case you are interested further, Owl Wing Thicket was once called the Temple of LuraŌĆÖvalas and was a place for worship for the goddess Elune. I may have diminished my practices of faith to her, but I still abide by her grace and judgement.$B$BNow, now; enough chitchat from me. I will repair the runestone, and as a thanks to you, will allow you to use it to visit my humble abode whenever curiosity strikes you. Feel free, it is my way of showing gratitude.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Who do you think is responsible for the runestone to malfunction? If you ask me, it mustŌĆÖve been those blue rascals near the lake. Their magic is so primitive, something had to go wrong eventually.'
WHERE `entry` = 42010;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I must admit, I was wrong. This crystal is different, certainly not a draenethyst. The mystery carries on.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I have yet to finish all my experiments on the draenethyst, yet I am very eager to see the other one.'
WHERE `entry` = 42011;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Your friend is bold, perhaps even a little dense. Yet a gift is a gift; I will welcome him the next time he comes. The crystal you took from the whelps is called a Starshard; it is the splinters of a meteor. There, mystery solved. Now, unless you have more draenethyst to offer, I will return to my duties.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Speak, traveler.'
WHERE `entry` = 42012;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So they truly were aggressive? Odd, to say the least. Why would druids of all people attack first and ask questions later?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The price for survival is high.'
WHERE `entry` = 42013;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good, the influence of LoŌĆÖsho is being dimmed; a task well done. Consider the Windhorn allowed to shadow my village for longer.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Serve them the justice of AnŌĆÖshe.'
WHERE `entry` = 42014;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Nature will take its course, and her body will return to dirt, as do all bodies. I pray LoŌĆÖsho saves her mind and lets her roam amongst the stars she once loved.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'She used to whisper the name of the stars to me.'
WHERE `entry` = 42015;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'With that, our tasks seem to have reached an end. You have done me and my people a good service. I will not forget this kindness.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Steel yourself, friend.'
WHERE `entry` = 42016;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I was half expecting you to mock me with the heart of a kodo, yet perhaps I judged you too rashly.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not fret, she is deemed an enemy to the village.'
WHERE `entry` = 42017;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ashtotem sends a humorous gift. He was meant to discuss diplomacy and alliances with the Moonhoof. Yet he was refused entry and decided to gift me the heart of MoonhoofŌĆÖs oldest friend, which he himself deemed an enemy now. How chaotic.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I did not summon any of you Horde whelps, so why is it you approach?'
WHERE `entry` = 42018;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You managed to find one. Good. Give it here and wait.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I could use a break.'
WHERE `entry` = 42019;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'ŌĆ£A gift from my brother. You have traveled far and wide to get to me; you have my deepest gratitude. To think my older brother put so much trust in my dreamŌĆöit pleases me. I will do this weapon great justice.ŌĆØ',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Something I can do for you, friend?'
WHERE `entry` = 42020;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It is done. While not as powerful as the original, this essence should be potent enough to douse the braziers spreading the WithermawŌĆÖs corruption throughout our sacred tunnels. If you require more, you know where to find me, brave adventurer.',
    `RequestItemsText` = '$N, I have heard of your continued assault on the darkness dwelling within Timbermaw Hold. It seems the salve I had created for you was not enough to quell the miasma. But fret not, as I am able to recreate the salve with a few ingredients. Bring them to me, and we shall resume our fight against evil.'
WHERE `entry` = 42021;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'For your acts for furbolgkind, you shall be rewarded honorably: A piece of armor to your liking handcrafted with the cleansed hide, so that you may walk the wilds under UrsolŌĆÖs blessing, continuing his legacy in fighting for the world he loved so much. Your presence here will remain welcoming in our retreat, as long as you remain true to our cause. Tread safely, $N.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Is this what they have done to our great god? Rotted him from the inside out, defiling his magnificent pelt and body? I dare not think about the agony he mustŌĆÖve endured during his torment. A relief to hear you have dealt with the traitors and have punished them justly.$B$BThe pelt of Ursol may be tainted, but with the purification salve Narkogg is brewing, we can cleanse it from the impurities. Bring it to me, and it shall be done.'
WHERE `entry` = 42022;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'There you have it, friend. Can you feel the spiritual energy coursing through? Those inexperienced will tremble at its might. So please, make good use of it against the foes of darkness.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Your contributions will be rewarded tenfold.'
WHERE `entry` = 42023;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'There you have it, friend. Can you feel the spiritual energy coursing through? Those inexperienced will tremble at its might. So please, make good use of it against the foes of darkness.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Your contributions will be rewarded tenfold.'
WHERE `entry` = 42024;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'There you have it, friend. Can you feel the spiritual energy coursing through? Those inexperienced will tremble at its might. So please, make good use of it against the foes of darkness.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Your contributions will be rewarded tenfold.'
WHERE `entry` = 42025;

