    `OfferRewardText` = 'There you have it, friend. Can you feel the spiritual energy coursing through? Those inexperienced will tremble at its might. So please, make good use of it against the foes of darkness.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Your contributions will be rewarded tenfold.'
WHERE `entry` = 42027;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'There you have it, friend. Can you feel the spiritual energy coursing through? Those inexperienced will tremble at its might. So please, make good use of it against the foes of darkness.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Your contributions will be rewarded tenfold.'
WHERE `entry` = 42028;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Jorach inspects the key with a meticulously thorough gaze. Tracing his fingers over its teeth, a wistful chuckle escapes the aged man.>$B$BIf this is not the most fortuitous coincidence. I believe what you have brought here will make us strike a most profitable deal, $N.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome back, agent. What dastardly deed has brought you back to my humble abode?'
WHERE `entry` = 42029;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Fascinating. I had my suspicions before, but according to the notes, weŌĆÖre dealing with something far more ancient than anticipated. How strange to see it in such an immaculate conditionŌĆ”',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'While I am most interested in the information they acquired, itŌĆÖd be most regrettable to ultimately lose such a fountain of knowledge by simply disposing of them. How refreshing it is that some old-fashioned blackmailing always does the trick to foster good working relations.'
WHERE `entry` = 42030;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Back so soon? Tremendous work, $N. ThereŌĆÖs no time for respite, however. WeŌĆÖve located the whereabouts of the blueprints to recreate the ancient elven lock. They were split apart into two pieces, each falling into the clutches of deranged fanatics. Stock up on supplies, young rogue, for even more danger awaits you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I wish you the most joyful adventure inside the Blackwing Lair. My agents and informants will continue our research regarding the lock blueprints.'
WHERE `entry` = 42031;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have my thanks, $N. I wish we could have sent more of them into purgatory, but neither do I have the men nor the time for such personal vendettas. For now, this shall suffice.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Carnelia was the beacon of light in this shadowy life of mine. I shall not have heathens like him sully her light without punishment.'
WHERE `entry` = 42032;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Excellent. Just what kind of parchment has been used for these blueprints baffles me greatly. The ancient highborne civilization must have been truly marvelous.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Powerful specters of the past reside within the crumbling ruins of Old Shadowforge. Trust your abilities and you should fare well against your enemies.'
WHERE `entry` = 42033;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Now thatŌĆÖs what I call proper payment. Now just wait a bit before I am done. Whatever you brought me here isnŌĆÖt exactly the easiest of readsŌĆ”',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Who are you and why are you interrupting my work? If youŌĆÖre here just to annoy me, then IŌĆÖll show you how hot my furnace really isŌĆ”$B$B<You explain your reason for being here and hand him the materials plus gold satchel.>$B$BOho, I see how it is. An express delivery, if you will. I may be the man for you, but if you need this done as soon as possible, this measly amount of gold wonŌĆÖt cut it. If you want this finished in record time, pass me another one-hundred gold and IŌĆÖll think about it. Deal?'
WHERE `entry` = 42034;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'My apologies. It seems my expenses were not enough for the old greedbeard. Fret not, however. See it as a unique opportunity for collaboration, strengthening our bond even further. Besides, arenŌĆÖt you excited to reap the rewards of your hard labor?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You have returned, hopefully with good news?'
WHERE `entry` = 42035;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'As instructed, you insert the lock into the indentation, which promptly springs into the contraption with a heavy clicking sound. Shortly after you insert the key, open the lid and welcome your just reward.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Jorach did not lie. Rarely have you seen a chest made with such a level of craftsmanship. Tiny ornaments and embellishments adorn the chest and an aura of mystique and magic exudes from it.'
WHERE `entry` = 42036;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Haha! You''ve done it, you''ve saved my arse!$B$BI was sure I was going to be back to Mountaineer duties if this ever got out. You''ve done me a real solid here, and for that you''ve earned something in return.$B$BOh, and don''t mention this, to anyone.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'If you''re seriously considering helping me out here it would mean a big deal. Just be careful, last thing I need is a casualty on top of losing these supplies.'
WHERE `entry` = 42037;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Got rid of those trolls have ye? Ironforge is just a little bit safer thanks to your actions, but now we can put our attentions at the real threats.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not let your guard down around those blasted trolls. They lack honor, and will strike even if you have your back turned.'
WHERE `entry` = 42038;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So, Ubukaz has been slain?$B$B<Granitebeard takes a moment, a smirk crossing his face.>$B$BI cannot believe my ears, I have no doubt there will be a another troll that shall rise to be chieftain, but for these coming days, peace shall be had in Dun Morogh.$B$BUntil their infighting is over, we have time to celebrate!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be prepared for anything $C, the Frostmane are a cunning foe.'
WHERE `entry` = 42039;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Ranix stares upon the tablet with interest gleaming on his eyes.>$B$BThis is it, wow, I did not think you would actually live up to your word on this! You did well, and since I am such an outstanding, and noble goblin I will pay you what your work is worth.$B$BI will be out of here soon enough, thanks again.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'So... Have you had any luck yet? I don''t want to spend too much longer down here if I don''t have too.'
WHERE `entry` = 42040;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Quit dawdling around! There''s no time to lose, youngster.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Ohoho! Seems I underestimated you, $C. Those vine cutters can practically slice air; and these rations are both filling and delicious! IŌĆÖm thoroughly impressed, you practically swept me off my feet with these. As promised, IŌĆÖll teach you some tips and tricks - tricks thatŌĆÖll help you survive even in the most hostile wilds imaginable.'
WHERE `entry` = 42041;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It pains me it had to come to this, but their delusions have brought them too far away from redemption. For the sake of nature and its inhabitants, they had to return to the cycle.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Whatever they hold in higher regard than my father Cenarius, it must be immensely powerful.'
WHERE `entry` = 42042;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Some look worse for wear, but none of them should truly be irreparable. Great work, $N. We will ensure that they arrive safely at Nighthaven, so that they can be properly archived once and for all. Thank you for your diligence, truly.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Beware, unseen powers linger in your adversaries. It is best to heed caution.'
WHERE `entry` = 42043;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Loganaar received my message? What a relief.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42044;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'But that is far from any of your problems - yet. You are still a novice, a whelpling tossed into this turbulent world. Yet still, you serve a purpose. To usher in a new age for dwarvenkind. Train in the forbidden arts of the arcane and grow more powerful. Seek my clan members and other mighty warlocks. With their knowledge, the king cannot but recognize that he needs us to save the kingdom.$B$BI may be still at the beginning of my journey too, but let me share what incantations I have learned by myself. Return to me often, and we shall exchange our wisdom of the shadowy arts.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Have you read the rune? Excellent!$B$BYou standing here before me signals to me that you are willing and eager enough to tread the journey only a few will master; and survive. My clan has seen the weakness that ails our ancient home, the vermin that scurry among the icy fields and dark mountain caves. If our people don''t accept any means necessary to exterminate those who do us harm, then Ironforge is doomed to perish.'
WHERE `entry` = 42045;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Fine feathers, you are better at this than I have anticipated.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Is the task proving to be more challenging than you expected?'
WHERE `entry` = 42046;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Your job is done and mine begins. I must tidy up the place now.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Often it feels like taking care of a kindergarten rather than a resting place in these lands.'
WHERE `entry` = 42047;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Groundstender RainhornŌĆÖs complaints? You must be kidding. I explained our situation to that old woman several times. Alas, I will send her a young bull or two.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Why do you bother me?'
WHERE `entry` = 42048;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Those of the Earthen Circle have deemed the shrines of Moonwhisper restless. And my aid is required to soothe them?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Boldly, you have sought an audience.'
WHERE `entry` = 42049;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I wonder if the Duke saw something in you. His words are not to be taken lightly. It is a great honor to be spoken to so reverently by the elements, especially one of such title. Speak to Lotka, your next quest awaits.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You return unharmed.'
WHERE `entry` = 42050;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Well done. With the help of water, the Earthen Ring and you, the elements rest. Knowing that their wrath is not yet required. The mortals of Moonwhisper Coast will face its turmoil with great conviction.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I am listening.'
WHERE `entry` = 42051;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It may seem mindless to many and to many it is. This hunt of dragons does not come simply at the whims of one orcŌĆÖs sport. Where these dragons were once meant to protect, they now seek to destroy.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Steel yourself. Only a few may walk the path of glory.'
WHERE `entry` = 42052;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Pick. One is my for the taking, yours is the other.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Tell me, what are you fighting for?'
WHERE `entry` = 42053;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It will be many cycles before you are ready to guide your hooves there, my friend. Your training resumes. Seek me once you have gained more experience in battle.$B$BTo be a devoted worshipper of the Celestial Siblings places you beyond the bounds of tribe. You are cherished by the eyes and the tear of the Earthmother. Whatever path you walk from now on, at least one of them will always be by your side.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Celestial Siblings guide your very first steps to me, $N. It is I who will watch over you and teach you what I can as you complete your training here in the Red Cloud Mesa.$B$BI trust you are eager to see the world for yourself and perhaps even walk a pilgrimage to the Moonwhisper Coast. Moonhoof Village holds three scrolls of prayer, each devoted to one of the Siblings.'
WHERE `entry` = 42054;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I have been expecting you, young blood.$B$BCome, let us speak. There are things you lack that you must learn, and I can teach them. But before I do, I sense a resolve in you. Has Nuhlok shared his love for LoŌĆÖsho with you? Good. Then allow me to share mine. I favor AnŌĆÖshe and, by default, all three of them. AnŌĆÖshe assumed the role of the elder sibling. It is by his light that the first children of the Earth, such as us, were born.$B$BHis graceful light nurtures our bodies and crops. It is the same light that illuminates MuŌĆÖsha and LoŌĆÖsho in the night sky, for without his light they could not be seen. Yet, like any elder, AnŌĆÖshe can be stubborn and judgmental, but he is just. He believes his path is the right one, for through his eyes it is the path of protection for both his worshippers and his siblings. A selfish yet benevolent patron, is he not?',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42055;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have done well. To commemorate your first trial, I will reward you with one of my old robes. As promised, let me speak of MuŌĆÖsha. One of our longest allies has been the night elves, who, as their name implies, are children of the Night and, as such, children of Elune, the name they have given MuŌĆÖsha. Through our years of connection, some tauren have sensed a trace of favoritism. If we are the children of the Earthmother, then the night elves are the children of MuŌĆÖsha, and she may seem inclined to favor them. That does not mean she neglects us in any way, yet a hint of jealousy lingers among some worshipers.$B$BIn truth, it has helped us bond with the night elves and find fraternity with them. But to speak plainly, MuŌĆÖsha has always pointed the way, and if you choose to follow it, do so. You do not need any explanation; she wonŌĆÖt try to convince you. Of the three, she is the most free, if you will. Her path is her own, and you can either come along or stay behind.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'You may see healing and enhancing your allies as extensions of both AnŌĆÖshe and MuŌĆÖsha. Where the rays of AnŌĆÖshe warmly soothe a wound, the white bloom in the night sky during each of MuŌĆÖshaŌĆÖs cycles acts as a guide through the darkness. LoŌĆÖsho can soothe, but he cannot heal. His gifts to you bend and mend the mind, not the body.'
WHERE `entry` = 42056;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It is time to indulge in the teachings of An''she, the Right Eye of the Earthmother. Let his light illuminate your way and blind those who wish to harm the Earthmother''s favored.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42057;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good to see you. Let us not waste any more time.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42058;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Lo''sho is often misunderstood, but he is as much a part of the Earthmother as both of her eyes. Close your eyes and listen to our people''s legends.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42059;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You''ve returned. It is time to open a new chapter in your spiritual journey.',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42060;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oh, thank the Light.$B$BAstalor finally sent someone. Good. Very good. I was beginning to think he hadŌĆ” forgotten.$B$BAs you can see, everything here is proceeding exactly as planned. Perfectly, even. Nothing has gone wrong. At all.$B$BThe expedition force isŌĆ” mostly intact. Entirely intact, really. I certainly did not lose most of it. That would be absurd.$B$BAnd even if I had, which I have not, the situation would still be well under control. Completely.$B$BStill. It isŌĆ” reassuring that you are here now.$B$BMy mission here is of great importance to our house. Critical, in fact. I simply require a bit ofŌĆ” assistance.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'A friendly face? Here?'
WHERE `entry` = 42061;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have seen it, I am certain. The corruption that grips this land. The twisted creatures that now call it home.$B$BThe Sentinels will not allow this suffering to continue. These shores are part of Kalimdor, and they will not be abandoned to darkness.$B$BBy oath and by duty, we will bring justice to this place. When the corruption is cleansed, peace will follow.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome to Narvalis Point.'
WHERE `entry` = 42062;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'From Velaya? OhŌĆ” you have no idea how long I have been waiting for this.$B$BI was starting to think she had forgotten me. A girl can only wait so long, you know.$B$B<IreaŌĆÖs smile brightens, the worry lifting from her face.>$B$BThank you, truly. This means more to me than you might think. I will have to write back to her soon. Very soon.$B$BIf you are staying the night, the first drink is on the house.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Greetings, friend.'
WHERE `entry` = 42063;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Good. This will keep us alive a while longer.$B$BDo not think this ends anything. The theft was not desperation - it was intent. They wanted to see how we would respond. Whether we were weak.$B$BNow they know better.$B$BThey will test us again. They always do. Wounded beasts grow bold when cornered. If we wait, they will gather, and they will come for us in the dark.$B$BNext time, we do not recover what was taken.$B$BNext time, we burn the hand that reaches for us.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'They are always watching.'
WHERE `entry` = 42064;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Forty heads.$B$BIt brings a measure of peace, seeing them laid out like that. Not enough, but some. We have only carved a dent in their numbers, nothing more.$B$BStill, it should give them pause. Fear lingers longer than pain, and they are not brave creatures when faced with open slaughter.$B$BWith luck, it will be enough to keep them from testing our encampment while we are still here.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Beware their daggers.$B$BThey coat the blades in venom not born of this world. It burns cold in the blood. I have watched strong warriors fall to their knees from a scratch no deeper than a thorn.$B$BDo not trust your armor to save you. Do not trust your healers to mend you in time. Even they struggle against that poison.'
WHERE `entry` = 42065;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Oh, these are potent.$B$BThe magic on them is still alive. Old, refined, dangerous. Otherworldly, even. And the craftsmanshipŌĆ” honestly, it is almost enough to make me nostalgic. Almost.$B$BYes, these are very much worth investigating. Possibly worth more than that, depending on who is asking.$B$BWell done, $C. You earned your keep.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The Highborne ghosts still think they are alive. They haunt the ruins, patrolling streets that no longer exist, guarding cities that fell centuries ago. In their minds, nothing has changed.$B$BThey will not part with their secrets willingly. Nor their artifacts. Expect resistance. Ferocious, stubborn, and very offended that you dare disturb their illusion.'
WHERE `entry` = 42066;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'SoŌĆ” you actually found one.$B$BYes. This resonance. I can feel it even through the wards. The arcane pattern is unstable, but not chaotic. That is rare. Very rare.$B$BYou did well to survive long enough to bring it back. Many would not have.$B$BWith this shard, the draenethyst may finally reveal its purpose. Or confirm my fears about it. Either outcome is preferable to ignorance.$B$BRest now. I will begin the work immediately, and carefully.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Proceed with caution.$B$BThe Fallen Ones are not to be underestimated. They are reckless, but not foolish, and they fight with a cruelty born of desperation.$B$BDo not take them lightly. Many have died that way.'
WHERE `entry` = 42067;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Our people have endured exile, betrayal, and slow decay, and still we stand. We will endure this as well. I believe that. I have to.$B$BThat said, belief alone will not carry us through what waits in that den. Pride has already cost us enough.$B$BI will admit this, if only once. I could use a steady hand at my side in this matter.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 42068;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'What is this?$B$B<Andanil stares into the artifact you retrieved. His eyes linger too long, as if it is staring back.>$B$BThis is it?$B$BYesŌĆ” of course it is. I see it now.$B$BThe magic is spent, drained dry, but there is no doubt. This is the source. This is what they found. Even emptied, it hums with purpose.$B$B<He lifts the object carefully, almost reverently, turning it in the light.>$B$BSuch precision. There is no waste here, no ornament for vanityŌĆÖs sake. This is not elven craft.$B$BI have studied relics from every corner of our past. Highborne vaults. Pre-Sundering ruins. Nothing even approaches this. Whatever made it did not think like us. It did not feel like us. And whatever power once flowed through it was enough to drain trained arcanists in moments and leave them wandering husks.$B$BAnd still, I cannot shake the feeling that this is only a shell. A key, perhaps. Something meant to be used again.$B$BI must return to AlahŌĆÖthalas at once.  Oh cousinŌĆ” this time, I did not fail you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not stray too far.$B$BThere is another Barrow Den farther north, within a druid grove. The druids there have made their feelings toward us very clear, and they were not welcoming.$B$BWhatever they guard is not meant for us, and I will not have you provoking another enemy while we are already stretched thin.$B$BStay away from that place.'
WHERE `entry` = 42069;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I understand the urgency of this request and I can surely feel for the Moonhoof heir. Were I in the same position I believe I would have done the same.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Welcome to Bloodhoof Village. Is there something you wish to tell me?'
WHERE `entry` = 42070;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You bring news from the Moonwhisper Coast and a favor from both the heir of the Moonhoof and mine? Sit, then, share this pipe with me and speak.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Come forth. This elder will listen.'
WHERE `entry` = 42071;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So they agreed to help. I must prepare something to thank them. When all of this is over, I will travel myself to Thunder Bluff to express my gratitude. Earthmother knows my father will not.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Are you the bearer of good news?'
WHERE `entry` = 42072;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Have you not said enough?',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 42073;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So he has revealed to you the reasons for his actions. He sought your help and knows death is one of the endings he might expect for his mistakes. Enough of that for now, tell me of this relic, and this letter you found.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Your audience with my father took more than I expected.'
WHERE `entry` = 42074;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'That will do. Keep your allies close, you will certainly need them for what comes next.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Alive, but is it by victory or cowardice?'
WHERE `entry` = 42075;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Thank you, now it is finally time to leave this damned place and return to the home I have lost. Farewell, member of the Horde. May we never cross paths again.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'How many have you gathered?'
WHERE `entry` = 42076;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So this marks the end. Arch Druid Mothshroud is gone, and Ireth Moondancer is still alive. He meant to strike the moon out of the sky. And he almost did, were you not here to stop him. We must report this to my father, but before we do, I believe a reward is in order for all your valiant deeds.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Whenever I send you on a task you somehow end up being gone longer than I expected. Tell me, have you found Moondancer?'
WHERE `entry` = 42077;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'I understand. I am not sure I am deserving of this mercy, or whether I would have given it myself were the roles reserved. I will accept my punishment and leave this village behind. It is time for another to lead then. With the help of his newfound allies, you included, he will certainly do far better than I.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I have felt his death. Does mine follow?'
WHERE `entry` = 42078;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have recovered this from the clutches of the demon that claimed the barrow den from the Grove of the Moon as home? Then, whatever lies on that paper is only for your eyes to see. Find a lone place and read it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Back for more training?'
WHERE `entry` = 42079;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'A bit of both then, member of the Horde. To what do I owe this untimely aid?',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Are you friend or foe? A bit of both then, member of the Horde. To what do I owe this untimely aid?'
WHERE `entry` = 42080;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Torgan sent you, did he?$B$B<Elder Starstrider''s features twist in annoyance>$B$BI suppose he is right. As much as I dislike our situation being aired out so openly.$B$B<The stubborn tauren snorts his displeasure of the situation, and how much Torgan may be correct.>$B$BWell, he is right, we do need help.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes, how is it that I can help you?'
WHERE `entry` = 42081;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Elder Starstrider gazes upon the feathers with aged and cold eyes, scanning them for imperfections>$B$BHmm... They are not in perfect condition, but they are good enough.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I must remind you, be gentle with the feathers when they are acquired, they are delicate!'
WHERE `entry` = 42082;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = '<Starstrider inspects the Rod for faults and damage, his eyes gazing over it with caution.>$B$BIt seems we have been spared a travesty. As crude as those little creatures are it would seem they have the foresight to not destroy everything in their clutches.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be wary of the Draenei, they are a cunning foe.'
WHERE `entry` = 42083;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'It has been a while since I have had my hands on such a rare material. You have done well, I have not expected this from a guest in our lands.$B$BIt would seem I have much to learn from outsiders such as yourself.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'I suggest you prepare yourself, this will be no easy task.'
WHERE `entry` = 42084;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Our Ancestors have delivered us quite the omen, and yet I am unsure of what to make of it... Regardless, another festival has been concluded, and without your help, I would still be waiting for assistance from Moonhoof Village.$B$BI must reward you for your generosity outsider. Please, take this, on behalf of myself, and all of those in my tribe. May your travels be gentle, and the road ahead free from burden.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 42085;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'AhŌĆ” yes.$B$B<Talanis carefully lifts one of the objects you recovered, turning it slowly in the light.>$B$BA childŌĆÖs carving knife. See the worn handle? Used for years. Passed from hand to hand, perhaps. And thisŌĆ” a moon pendant. The silverwork is crude, but earnest. Likely made by someone learning their craft.$B$B<He exhales quietly.>$B$BThirty small pieces of a forgotten life. That is what you have brought me. History is not only written in great battles and kings, you know. Sometimes it survives in the things ordinary people carried with them each day. Thank you for retrieving these, $C. The naga may have taken the town, but they will not erase its memory.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Take care while you search the ruins. Even the smallest relic may hold a story worth remembering.'
WHERE `entry` = 42086;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'SoŌĆ” it truly remained there all this time.$B$B<Talanis studies the artifact in silence for a long moment.>$B$BRemarkable. The craftsmanship alone places it centuries before the founding of Zin-Azshari. And the lunar resonanceŌĆ” yes, I can feel it even now. This was no mere ceremonial piece. It was used. Studied. Revered. The priestesses of Elunaris must have trained beneath its light, learning to channel EluneŌĆÖs blessing through it.$B$BYou have brought back more than a relic today. You have returned a fragment of our past that might otherwise have vanished with the temple itself.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Now, the maddened druids and their lackeys walk in these once sacred halls. Be wary.'
WHERE `entry` = 42087;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So it is done.$B$BI take no satisfaction in this. StillŌĆ” if they had been left unchecked, more would have died. We will keep watch on the rest of their tribes. If this corruption spreads, we will know. Until then, Narvalis Point remains secure. That is what matters.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Tauren are formidable opponents. Their strength alone is enough to shatter shields and bones alike. Do not let their size fool you into thinking them slow.'
WHERE `entry` = 42088;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Thirty scales.$B$B<She turns one over in her gauntleted hand, inspecting the deep green sheen.>$B$BThese belonged to seasoned warriors. Killing this many will have been noticed among their ranks.$B$BGood.$B$BStillŌĆ” their true leaders remain. And until they fall, the Tideblade will not abandon these ruins.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Watch the water. Naga favor ambush. They will wait beneath the surface until you step too close to the shore. More than one patrol has learned that lesson the hard way.'
WHERE `entry` = 42089;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Lady SerpentiaŌĆ” and TaŌĆÖjax as well.$B$B<For the first time, Silverstreak allows herself a small, satisfied nod.>$B$BGood. Very good.$B$BWithout them, the Tideblade will splinter into rival broods. Naga are not known for unity when strong leaders are absent. That gives us the advantage. The ruins of Nendis may finally know peace again.$B$BThe High Priestess should hear of it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not underestimate them.$B$BThese two commanded armies during IllidanŌĆÖs campaign. They survived battles that slaughtered hundreds.$B$BCreatures like that do not fall easily.'
WHERE `entry` = 42090;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Lady Serpentia and TaŌĆÖjax are dead?$B$BThose names were spoken often during the war against Illidan. Their warbands left scars along this coast that have not yet faded. If they have truly fallen, then one of the last shadows from that time has finally been lifted.$B$BNendis has been silent for far too long. With the naga driven out, the ruins may finally be reclaimed. Not quickly. Wounds like these take time to heal. But in timeŌĆ” our people will return. Homes will be rebuilt. Temples restored. The forests will hear our voices again.$B$BMoonwhisper Coast was once a place where the kaldorei lived in peace beneath EluneŌĆÖs light. Perhaps, slowly, it may become so again.$B$BYou have helped make that future possible, $C. Know that the sentinels of Narvalis Point have my gratitudeŌĆ” and so do you.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 42091;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Starcaller is dead?$B$BGood. That removes the most immediate obstacle.$B$BThe blue dragonflight rarely commits to guarding something so aggressively unless it carries great arcane significance.$B$BA meteor saturated with arcane energyŌĆ” and dragons circling it like vultures.$B$BYes. There is definitely more to this crater than a simple rock from the sky. With that drake gone, perhaps the others will grow less bold. Or perhaps they will become curious enough to reveal what they were truly protecting.$B$BEither way, you have given us an opportunity to learn the truth.$B$BAnd I very much intend to take it.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Starcaller will not fight like the creatures you are used to.$B$BBlue dragons wield arcane power as easily as most people breathe. Expect spells. Expect sudden bursts of energy that turn the air itself against you.$B$BAnd if the meteor truly empowers the creatureŌĆ”Then the fight may be more interesting than I anticipated.'
WHERE `entry` = 42092;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ah, excellent feathers.$B$B<Elendon runs one of them between his fingers, testing its strength.>$B$BSee the structure along the spine? Flexible, but firm. That is exactly what we need. With these I can finish a proper batch of arrows. The sentinels will appreciate the difference the next time they loose a volley across the treeline.$B$BYou have my thanks, $C.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Take care when approaching the hippogryphs. They are not hostile by nature, but they defend their nests fiercely. If one takes flight above you, keep your eyes open. They strike from the air faster than most people expect.'
WHERE `entry` = 42093;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'So the grove has been quietedŌĆ” for now.$B$BI hoped the corruption had not spread this far, but the signs are unmistakable. These druids no longer serve the balance of the wilds. Something has guided them down this path.$B$BThe Grove of the Sun on the Isle of Tyrandas may hold answers. One of my allies tends the groves there.$B$BSeek out Sister Mirallun. She watches the forest more closely than most. Tell her what you have seen.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Be wary when dealing with druids who have abandoned balance.They still wield the same powers we do. The Dream still answers themŌĆ” though it should not.$B$BThat alone makes them dangerous.'
WHERE `entry` = 42094;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'The Grove of the Moon has fallen to them as well?$B$BI had feared as much.$B$BThe forest has been restless for many nights now. Roots twist where they should grow straight. Dreams drift through the groves where none should linger.$B$BThe corruption runs deeper than a single grove.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Yes?'
WHERE `entry` = 42095;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have done what was necessary.$B$BThe forest breathes a little easier already.$B$BBut the druids who began this corruption still remainŌĆ” and one of them leads the others.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Do not linger too long in ElunŌĆÖaran.$B$BThe forest there no longer dreams peacefully. Something darker watches through its roots.'
WHERE `entry` = 42096;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Krothis has fallenŌĆ”$B$BThe forest mourns when a keeper dies, even one who lost his way.$B$BWithout Krothis guiding them, the corrupted druids will scatter. Some may yet remember the teachings they abandoned.$B$BOthers will follow Mothshroud deeper into shadow.$B$BThis is not the end of the matter. If Mothshroud truly walks these lands again, then the groves face a danger older than most remember.$B$BBut for now, the forest breathes a little easier.$B$BYou have done well.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Krothis was once a keeper of the grove. Creatures like that do not fall easily and those who follow Mothshroud rarely fight alone.'
WHERE `entry` = 42097;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Excellent work, $N. Now that they''ve been driven back, we can fortify our position against future assaults!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Stand proud, soldier. Sharpen your wits and bolster your courage, then this battle will be swiftly done.'
WHERE `entry` = 42098;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Well fought, $N! Now that they have been beaten, they''ll scurry back into the laps of the Alliance. This day marks our triumphant victory!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'The dwarves and their allies are not shy of using underhanded tactics to ensure the success of their mission. Do not let them get the upper hand!'
WHERE `entry` = 42099;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Just what is this?! A crate filled to the brim with clothes, food, toys and the like? Where have you found this, good friend? Was it perhaps a miracle from Alonsus Faol himself, watching over his culvers from beyond the veil? Whatever it may be, we must thank the Light for showing us yet again that the selfless and righteous will not be left alone in darkness.$B$B$N, my eternal thanks to you. Now, I should not waste any more time. The poor are waiting for me. Please take this from gracious gifts you have found, you more than deserve a reward yourself. May the Light bless your journey!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'May the Light bestow guidance upon you, so that the poor be graced by its benevolence.'
WHERE `entry` = 42100;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'An entire crate full of food, cloth and instruments?! How is this possible? Could this really be a blessing of the Earthmother? It must be! I can''t believe we are this fortunate. Proven again and again, she provides for her people and those that cherish her throughout their lives.$B$B$N, I have to thank you from the bottom of my heart. With your aid, we can yet organize and plan the feast in honor of her benevolence. Please, take this reward from the bounty you have brought us. You have more than deserved this reward. Go with the Earthmother''s blessing, $N.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Sprites of nature are said to be messengers of luck and fortune. I am certain that is what I saw.'
WHERE `entry` = 42101;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Great! A student! Listen to me carefully...',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 50000;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'You have done well, his head is in perfect conditions. Come closer and I will show you how to disguise as a filthy human.$B$BDon''t forget your class notes!',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'Come on! Bring me his head, I don''t have all day.'
WHERE `entry` = 50002;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Great! A student! Listen to me carefully...',
    `RequestItemsText` = ''
WHERE `entry` = 50003;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
    `OfferRewardText` = 'Ma always said, ŌĆ£Waste not, want not!ŌĆØ$B$BI really took that to heart and started ŌĆ£repurposingŌĆØ the creatures that I could get away with doppleganging as. Goblins, kobolds, troggs... things like that.$B$BWhat, you don''t think I can look like this orc? Maybe I can''t, but you definitely can.$B$BThere''s a bunch of other disguises out in the world if you''re crafty enough. You just have to go and find ''em.$B$BTake these notes with you, and good luck with your game of charades.',
    `RequestItemsText` = 'What''re you waitin'' for? I ain''t got all day, bub. Bring me the drunk orc''s head.'
WHERE `entry` = 50004;

UPDATE `quest_template` SET
